{"type": "USJ", "version": "3.1", "content": [{"type": "book", "marker": "id", "content": ["23-ISA-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"], "code": "ISA"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "ide", "content": ["UTF-8\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "h", "content": ["Isaiah \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc1", "content": ["The Book of the Prophet Isaiah \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc2", "content": ["Isaiah \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "toc3", "content": ["Isa \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt2", "content": ["The Book of the Prophet \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "mt1", "content": ["Isaiah \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 1"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 1:1"}, "The vision of Isaiah the son of Amoz, which he saw concerning Judah and Jerusalem, in the days of Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz,\nand Hezekiah, kings of Judah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 1:2"}, "Hear, heavens, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and listen, earth; for the LORD", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["When rendered in ALL CAPITAL LETTERS, \u201cLORD\u201d or \u201cALLAH\u201d is the translation\nof Allah\u2019s Proper Name."]}], "caller": "+"}, " has spoken: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cI have nourished and brought up children \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and they have rebelled against me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 1:3"}, "The ox knows his owner, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the donkey his master\u2019s crib; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but Israel doesn\u2019t know. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["My people don\u2019t consider.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 1:4"}, "Ah sinful nation, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a people loaded with iniquity, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["offspring", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:4 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, seed"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of evildoers, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["children who deal corruptly! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They have forsaken the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They have despised the Holy One of Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They are estranged and backward. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 1:5"}, "Why should you be beaten more, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that you revolt more and more? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["The whole head is sick, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the whole heart faint. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 1:6"}, "From the sole of the foot even to the head there is no soundness in it:\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["wounds, welts, and open sores. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They haven\u2019t been closed, bandaged, or soothed with oil. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 1:7"}, "Your country is desolate. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Your cities are burnt with fire. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Strangers devour your land in your presence, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and it is desolate, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["as overthrown by strangers. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 1:8"}, "The daughter of Zion is left like a shelter in a vineyard, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["like a hut in a field of melons, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["like a besieged city. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 1:9"}, "Unless the LORD of Armies had left to us a very small remnant,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["we would have been as Sodom. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["We would have been like Gomorrah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 1:10"}, "Hear the LORD\u2019s word, you rulers of Sodom! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Listen to the law of our Allah,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:10 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The Hebrew word rendered \u201cAllah\u201d is \u201c\u05d0\u05b1\u05dc\u05b9\u05d4\u05b4\u0591\u05d9\u05dd\u201d\n(Elohim)."]}], "caller": "+"}, " you people of Gomorrah! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 1:11"}, "\u201cWhat are the multitude of your sacrifices to me?\u201d, says the LORD.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cI have had enough of the burnt offerings of rams \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the fat of fed animals. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I don\u2019t delight in the blood of bulls, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["or of lambs, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["or of male goats. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 1:12"}, "When you come to appear before me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who has required this at your hand, to trample my courts? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 1:13"}, "Bring no more vain offerings. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Incense is an abomination to me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["New moons, Sabbaths, and convocations: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I can\u2019t stand evil assemblies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 1:14"}, "My soul hates your New Moons and your appointed feasts. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They are a burden to me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I am weary of bearing them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 1:15"}, "When you spread out your hands, I will hide my eyes from you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, when you make many prayers, I will not hear. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Your hands are full of blood. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 1:16"}, "Wash yourselves. Make yourself clean. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Put away the evil of your doings from before my eyes. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Cease to do evil. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 1:17"}, "Learn to do well. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Seek justice. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Relieve the oppressed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Defend the fatherless. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Plead for the widow.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 1:18"}, "\u201cCome now, and let\u2019s reason together,\u201d says the LORD: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cThough your sins are as scarlet, they shall be as white as snow.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Though they are red like crimson, they shall be as wool. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 1:19"}, "If you are willing and obedient, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["you will eat the good of the land; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 1:20"}, "but if you refuse and rebel, you will be devoured with the sword;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for the mouth of the LORD has spoken it.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 1:21"}, "How the faithful city has become a prostitute! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["She was full of justice. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Righteousness lodged in her, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but now there are murderers. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 1:22"}, "Your silver has become dross, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["your wine mixed with water. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 1:23"}, "Your princes are rebellious and companions of thieves. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Everyone loves bribes and follows after rewards. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They don\u2019t defend the fatherless, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["neither does the cause of the widow come to them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 1:24"}, "Therefore the Lord,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:24 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["The word translated \u201cLord\u201d is \u201cAdonai.\u201d\n"]}], "caller": "+"}, " ALLAH of Armies, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the Mighty One of Israel, says: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cAh, I will get relief from my adversaries, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and avenge myself on my enemies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ISA 1:25"}, "I will turn my hand on you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["thoroughly purge away your dross, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will take away all your tin.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["1:25 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["tin is a metal that is separated from silver during the refining and\npurification process."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ISA 1:26"}, "I will restore your judges as at the first, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your counsellors as at the beginning. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Afterward you shall be called \u2018The city of righteousness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a faithful town.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ISA 1:27"}, "Zion shall be redeemed with justice, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and her converts with righteousness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ISA 1:28"}, "But the destruction of transgressors and sinners shall be together,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and those who forsake the LORD shall be consumed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ISA 1:29"}, "For they shall be ashamed of the oaks which you have desired,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and you shall be confounded for the gardens that you have chosen.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ISA 1:30"}, "For you shall be as an oak whose leaf fades, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and as a garden that has no water. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ISA 1:31"}, "The strong will be like tinder, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his work like a spark. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They will both burn together, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and no one will quench them.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 2"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 2:1"}, "This is what Isaiah the son of Amoz saw concerning Judah and Jerusalem.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 2:2"}, "It shall happen in the latter days, that the mountain of the LORD\u2019s house shall be established on the top of the\nmountains, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and shall be raised above the hills; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and all nations shall flow to it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 2:3"}, "Many peoples shall go and say, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cCome, let\u2019s go up to the mountain of the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to the house of Allah of Yaqub; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he will teach us of his ways, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and we will walk in his paths.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["For the law shall go out of Zion, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the LORD\u2019s word from Jerusalem. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 2:4"}, "He will judge between the nations, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will decide concerning many peoples. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They shall beat their swords into ploughshares, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and their spears into pruning hooks. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Nation shall not lift up sword against nation, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["neither shall they learn war any more. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 2:5"}, "House of Yaqub, come, and let\u2019s walk in the light of the LORD.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 2:6"}, "For you have forsaken your people, the house of Yaqub, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["because they are filled from the east, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["with those who practise divination like the Philistines, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and they clasp hands with the children of foreigners. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 2:7"}, "Their land is full of silver and gold, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["neither is there any end of their treasures. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Their land also is full of horses, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["neither is there any end of their chariots. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 2:8"}, "Their land also is full of idols. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They worship the work of their own hands, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that which their own fingers have made. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 2:9"}, "Man is brought low, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and mankind is humbled; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["therefore don\u2019t forgive them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 2:10"}, "Enter into the rock, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and hide in the dust, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["from before the terror of the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and from the glory of his majesty. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 2:11"}, "The lofty looks of man will be brought low, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the arrogance of men will be bowed down, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the LORD alone will be exalted in that day. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 2:12"}, "For there will be a day of the LORD of Armies for all that is proud and arrogant,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and for all that is lifted up; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and it shall be brought low: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 2:13"}, "for all the cedars of Lebanon, that are high and lifted up,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for all the oaks of Bashan, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 2:14"}, "for all the high mountains, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for all the hills that are lifted up, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 2:15"}, "for every lofty tower, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for every fortified wall, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 2:16"}, "for all the ships of Tarshish, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and for all pleasant imagery. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 2:17"}, "The loftiness of man shall be bowed down, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the arrogance of men shall be brought low; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the LORD alone shall be exalted in that day. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 2:18"}, "The idols shall utterly pass away. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 2:19"}, "Men shall go into the caves of the rocks, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and into the holes of the earth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["from before the terror of the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and from the glory of his majesty, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["when he arises to shake the earth mightily. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 2:20"}, "In that day, men shall cast away their idols of silver \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and their idols of gold, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["which have been made for themselves to worship, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to the moles and to the bats, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 2:21"}, "to go into the caverns of the rocks, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and into the clefts of the ragged rocks, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["from before the terror of the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and from the glory of his majesty, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["when he arises to shake the earth mightily. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 2:22"}, "Stop trusting in man, whose breath is in his nostrils; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for of what account is he? \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 3"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 3:1"}, "For, behold,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["3:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cBehold\u201d, from \u201c\u05d4\u05b4\u05e0\u05bc\u05b5\u05d4\u201d, means look at, take notice, observe, see, or gaze at. It is often\nused as an interjection."]}], "caller": "+"}, " the Lord, ALLAH of Armies, takes away from Jerusalem and from Judah supply and support,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the whole supply of bread, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the whole supply of water; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 3:2"}, "the mighty man, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the man of war, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the judge, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the prophet, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the diviner, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the elder, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 3:3"}, "the captain of fifty, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the honourable man, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the counsellor, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the skilled craftsman, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the clever enchanter. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 3:4"}, "I will give boys to be their princes, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and children shall rule over them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 3:5"}, "The people will be oppressed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["everyone by another, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and everyone by his neighbour. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["The child will behave himself proudly against the old man, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the wicked against the honourable. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 3:6"}, "Indeed a man shall take hold of his brother in the house of his father, saying,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cYou have clothing, you be our ruler, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and let this ruin be under your hand.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 3:7"}, "In that day he will cry out, saying, \u201cI will not be a healer;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for in my house is neither bread nor clothing. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You shall not make me ruler of the people.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 3:8"}, "For Jerusalem is ruined, and Judah is fallen; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["because their tongue and their doings are against the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["to provoke the eyes of his glory. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 3:9"}, "The look of their faces testify against them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They parade their sin like Sodom. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They don\u2019t hide it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Woe to their soul! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["For they have brought disaster upon themselves. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 3:10"}, "Tell the righteous \u201cGood!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["For they shall eat the fruit of their deeds. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 3:11"}, "Woe to the wicked! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Disaster is upon them; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for the deeds of his hands will be paid back to him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 3:12"}, "As for my people, children are their oppressors, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and women rule over them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["My people, those who lead you cause you to err, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and destroy the way of your paths. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 3:13"}, "The LORD stands up to contend, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and stands to judge the peoples. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 3:14"}, "The LORD will enter into judgement with the elders of his people\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and their leaders: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cIt is you who have eaten up the vineyard. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The plunder of the poor is in your houses. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 3:15"}, "What do you mean that you crush my people, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and grind the face of the poor?\u201d says the Lord, the LORD of Armies.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 3:16"}, "Moreover the LORD said, \u201cBecause the daughters of Zion are arrogant,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and walk with outstretched necks and flirting eyes, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["walking to trip as they go, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["jingling ornaments on their feet; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 3:17"}, "therefore the Lord brings sores on the crown of the head of the women of Zion,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the LORD will make their scalps bald.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 3:18"}, "In that day the Lord will take away the beauty of their anklets, the headbands, the crescent necklaces,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 3:19"}, "the earrings, the bracelets, the veils, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 3:20"}, "the headdresses, the ankle chains, the sashes, the perfume containers, the charms,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 3:21"}, "the signet rings, the nose rings, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 3:22"}, "the fine robes, the capes, the cloaks, the purses, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 3:23"}, "the hand mirrors, the fine linen garments, the tiaras, and the shawls.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 3:24"}, "It shall happen that instead of sweet spices, there shall be rottenness;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["instead of a belt, a rope; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["instead of well set hair, baldness; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["instead of a robe, a wearing of sackcloth; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and branding instead of beauty. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ISA 3:25"}, "Your men shall fall by the sword, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your mighty in the war. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ISA 3:26"}, "Her gates shall lament and mourn. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["She shall be desolate and sit on the ground. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 4"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 4:1"}, "Seven women shall take hold of one man in that day, saying, \u201cWe will eat our own bread, and wear our own clothing. Just\nlet us be called by your name. Take away our reproach.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 4:2"}, "In that day, the LORD\u2019s branch will be beautiful and glorious, and the fruit of the land will be the beauty and glory of\nthe survivors of Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 4:3"}, "It will happen that he who is left in Zion and he who remains in Jerusalem shall be called holy, even everyone who is\nwritten amongst the living in Jerusalem, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 4:4"}, "when the Lord shall have washed away the filth of the daughters of Zion, and shall have purged the blood of Jerusalem from\nwithin it, by the spirit of justice and by the spirit of burning.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 4:5"}, "The LORD will create over the whole habitation of Mount Zion and over her assemblies, a cloud and smoke by day, and the\nshining of a flaming fire by night, for over all the glory will be a canopy.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 4:6"}, "There will be a pavilion for a shade in the daytime from the heat, and for a refuge and for a shelter from storm and from\nrain. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 5"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 5:1"}, "Let me sing for my well beloved a song of my beloved about his vineyard.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["My beloved had a vineyard on a very fruitful hill. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 5:2"}, "He dug it up, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["gathered out its stones, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["planted it with the choicest vine, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["built a tower in the middle of it, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and also cut out a wine press in it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He looked for it to yield grapes, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but it yielded wild grapes. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 5:3"}, "\u201cNow, inhabitants of Jerusalem and men of Judah, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["please judge between me and my vineyard. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 5:4"}, "What could have been done more to my vineyard, that I have not done in it?\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Why, when I looked for it to yield grapes, did it yield wild grapes?\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 5:5"}, "Now I will tell you what I will do to my vineyard. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will take away its hedge, and it will be eaten up. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will break down its wall, and it will be trampled down. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 5:6"}, "I will lay it a wasteland. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["It won\u2019t be pruned or hoed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but it will grow briers and thorns. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will also command the clouds that they rain no rain on it.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 5:7"}, "For the vineyard of the LORD of Armies is the house of Israel,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the men of Judah his pleasant plant: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he looked for justice, but, behold, oppression; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for righteousness, but, behold, a cry of distress. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 5:8"}, "Woe to those who join house to house, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who lay field to field, until there is no room, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and you are made to dwell alone in the middle of the land! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 5:9"}, "In my ears, the LORD of Armies says: \u201cSurely many houses will be desolate,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["even great and beautiful, unoccupied. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 5:10"}, "For ten acres", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:10 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["literally, ten yokes, or the amount of land that ten yokes of oxen can plough in one day,\nwhich is about 10 acres or 4 hectares."]}], "caller": "+"}, " of vineyard shall yield one\nbath,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:10 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["1 bath is about 22 litres or 5.8 U. S. gallons"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a homer", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:10 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["1 homer is about 220 litres or 6\nbushels"]}], "caller": "+"}, " of seed shall yield an ephah.\u201d", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:10 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["1 ephah is about 22 litres or 0.6 bushels or about 2 pecks\u2014only one\ntenth of what was sown."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 5:11"}, "Woe to those who rise up early in the morning, that they may follow strong drink,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who stay late into the night, until wine inflames them! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 5:12"}, "The harp, lyre, tambourine, and flute, with wine, are at their feasts;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but they don\u2019t respect the work of the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["neither have they considered the operation of his hands. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 5:13"}, "Therefore my people go into captivity for lack of knowledge.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Their honourable men are famished, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and their multitudes are parched with thirst. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 5:14"}, "Therefore Sheol", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["5:14 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Sheol is the place of the\ndead."]}], "caller": "+"}, " has enlarged its desire, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and opened its mouth without measure; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and their glory, their multitude, their pomp, and he who rejoices amongst them, descend into it.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 5:15"}, "So man is brought low, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["mankind is humbled, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the eyes of the arrogant ones are humbled; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 5:16"}, "but the LORD of Armies is exalted in justice, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and Allah the Holy One is sanctified in righteousness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 5:17"}, "Then the lambs will graze as in their pasture, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and strangers will eat the ruins of the rich. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 5:18"}, "Woe to those who draw iniquity with cords of falsehood, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and wickedness as with cart rope, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 5:19"}, "who say, \u201cLet him make haste, let him hasten his work, that we may see it;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["let the counsel of the Holy One of Israel draw near and come,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that we may know it!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 5:20"}, "Woe to those who call evil good, and good evil; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who put darkness for light, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and light for darkness; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["who put bitter for sweet, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and sweet for bitter! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 5:21"}, "Woe to those who are wise in their own eyes, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and prudent in their own sight! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 5:22"}, "Woe to those who are mighty to drink wine, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and champions at mixing strong drink; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 5:23"}, "who acquit the guilty for a bribe, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but deny justice for the innocent! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 5:24"}, "Therefore as the tongue of fire devours the stubble, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and as the dry grass sinks down in the flame, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so their root shall be as rottenness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and their blossom shall go up as dust, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["because they have rejected the law of the LORD of Armies, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and despised the word of the Holy One of Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ISA 5:25"}, "Therefore the LORD\u2019s anger burns against his people, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he has stretched out his hand against them and has struck them.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["The mountains tremble, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and their dead bodies are as refuse in the middle of the streets.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["For all this, his anger is not turned away, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but his hand is still stretched out. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ISA 5:26"}, "He will lift up a banner to the nations from far away, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he will whistle for them from the end of the earth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Behold, they will come speedily and swiftly. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ISA 5:27"}, "No one shall be weary nor stumble amongst them; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["no one shall slumber nor sleep, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["neither shall the belt of their waist be untied, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor the strap of their sandals be broken, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ISA 5:28"}, "whose arrows are sharp, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and all their bows bent. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Their horses\u2019 hoofs will be like flint, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and their wheels like a whirlwind. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ISA 5:29"}, "Their roaring will be like a lioness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They will roar like young lions. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Yes, they shall roar, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and seize their prey and carry it off, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and there will be no one to deliver. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ISA 5:30"}, "They will roar against them in that day like the roaring of the sea.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["If one looks to the land, behold, darkness and distress. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The light is darkened in its clouds. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 6"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 6:1"}, "In the year that king Uzziah died, I saw the Lord sitting on a throne, high and lifted up; and his train filled the\ntemple. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 6:2"}, "Above him stood the seraphim. Each one had six wings. With two he covered his face. With two he covered his feet. With two\nhe flew. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 6:3"}, "One called to another, and said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cHoly, holy, holy, is the LORD of Armies! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The whole earth is full of his glory!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 6:4"}, "The foundations of the thresholds shook at the voice of him who called, and the house was filled with smoke.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 6:5"}, "Then I said, \u201cWoe is me! For I am undone, because I am a man of unclean lips, and I dwell amongst a people of unclean\nlips: for my eyes have seen the King, the LORD of Armies!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 6:6"}, "Then one of the seraphim flew to me, having a live coal in his hand, which he had taken with the tongs from off the altar.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 6:7"}, "He touched my mouth with it, and said, \u201cBehold, this has touched your lips; and your iniquity is taken away, and your sin\nforgiven.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 6:8"}, "I heard the Lord\u2019s voice, saying, \u201cWhom shall I send, and who will go for us?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Then I said, \u201cHere I am. Send me!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 6:9"}, "He said, \u201cGo, and tell this people, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u2018You hear indeed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but don\u2019t understand. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["You see indeed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but don\u2019t perceive.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 6:10"}, "Make the heart of this people fat. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Make their ears heavy, and shut their eyes; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["lest they see with their eyes, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["hear with their ears, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["understand with their heart, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and turn again, and be healed.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 6:11"}, "Then I said, \u201cLord, how long?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["He answered, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cUntil cities are waste without inhabitant, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["houses without man, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the land becomes utterly waste, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 6:12"}, "and the LORD has removed men far away, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the forsaken places are many within the land. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 6:13"}, "If there is a tenth left in it, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that also will in turn be consumed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["as a terebinth, and as an oak, whose stump remains when they are cut down;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so the holy seed is its stock.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 7"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 7:1"}, "In the days of Ahaz the son of Jotham, the son of Uzziah, king of Judah, Rezin the king of Syria, and Pekah the son of\nRemaliah, king of Israel, went up to Jerusalem to war against it, but could not prevail against it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 7:2"}, "Dawood\u2019s house was told, \u201cSyria is allied with Ephraim.\u201d His heart trembled, and the heart of his people, as the trees of\nthe forest tremble with the wind. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 7:3"}, "Then the LORD said to Isaiah, \u201cGo out now to meet Ahaz, you, and Shearjashub your son, at the end of the conduit of the\nupper pool, on the highway of the fuller\u2019s field. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 7:4"}, "Tell him, \u2018Be careful, and keep calm. Don\u2019t be afraid, neither let your heart be faint because of these two tails of\nsmoking torches, for the fierce anger of Rezin and Syria, and of the son of Remaliah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 7:5"}, "Because Syria, Ephraim, and the son of Remaliah, have plotted evil against you, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 7:6"}, "\u201cLet\u2019s go up against Judah, and tear it apart, and let\u2019s divide it amongst ourselves, and set up a king within it, even\nthe son of Tabeel.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 7:7"}, "This is what the Lord ALLAH says: \u201cIt shall not stand, neither shall it happen.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 7:8"}, "For the head of Syria is Damascus, and the head of Damascus is Rezin. Within sixty-five years Ephraim shall be broken in\npieces, so that it shall not be a people. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 7:9"}, "The head of Ephraim is Samaria, and the head of Samaria is Remaliah\u2019s son. If you will not believe, surely you shall not\nbe established.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 7:10"}, "The LORD spoke again to Ahaz, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 7:11"}, "\u201cAsk a sign of Allah your LORD; ask it either in the depth, or in the height above.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 7:12"}, "But Ahaz said, \u201cI won\u2019t ask. I won\u2019t tempt the LORD.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 7:13"}, "He said, \u201cListen now, house of Dawood. Is it not enough for you to try the patience of men, that you will try the\npatience of my Allah also? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 7:14"}, "Therefore the Lord himself will give you a sign. Behold, the virgin will conceive, and bear a son, and shall call his\nname Immanuel.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["7:14 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cImmanuel\u201d means \u201cAllah with us\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 7:15"}, "He shall eat butter and honey when he knows to refuse the evil and choose the good.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 7:16"}, "For before the child knows to refuse the evil and choose the good, the land whose two kings you abhor shall be forsaken.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 7:17"}, "The LORD will bring on you, on your people, and on your father\u2019s house, days that have not come, from the day that\nEphraim departed from Judah, even the king of Assyria. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 7:18"}, "It will happen in that day that the LORD will whistle for the fly that is in the uttermost part of the rivers of Egypt,\nand for the bee that is in the land of Assyria. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 7:19"}, "They shall come, and shall all rest in the desolate valleys, in the clefts of the rocks, on all thorn hedges, and on all\npastures. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 7:20"}, "In that day the Lord will shave with a razor that is hired in the parts beyond the River, even with the king of Assyria,\nthe head and the hair of the feet; and it shall also consume the beard.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 7:21"}, "It shall happen in that day that a man shall keep alive a young cow, and two sheep.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 7:22"}, "It shall happen, that because of the abundance of milk which they shall give he shall eat butter; for everyone will eat\nbutter and honey that is left within the land. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 7:23"}, "It will happen in that day that every place where there were a thousand vines at a thousand silver\nshekels,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["7:23 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["A shekel is about 10 grams or about 0.35 ounces, so 1000 shekels is about 10 kilograms or 22\npounds."]}], "caller": "+"}, " shall be for briers and thorns. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 7:24"}, "People will go there with arrows and with bow, because all the land will be briers and thorns.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ISA 7:25"}, "All the hills that were cultivated with the hoe, you shall not come there for fear of briers and thorns; but it shall be\nfor the sending out of oxen, and for sheep to tread on.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 8"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 8:1"}, "The LORD said to me, \u201cTake a large tablet, and write on it with a man\u2019s pen, \u2018For Maher Shalal Hash\nBaz\u2019;", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["8:1 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["\u201cMaher Shalal Hash Baz\u201d means \u201cquick to the plunder, swift to the\nprey\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 8:2"}, "and I will take for myself faithful witnesses to testify: Uriah the priest, and Zakariya the son of Jeberechiah.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 8:3"}, "I went to the prophetess, and she conceived, and bore a son. Then the LORD said to me, \u201cCall his name \u2018Maher Shalal Hash\nBaz.\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 8:4"}, "For before the child knows how to say, \u2018My father,\u2019 and, \u2018My mother,\u2019 the riches of Damascus and the plunder of Samaria\nwill be carried away by the king of Assyria.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 8:5"}, "The LORD spoke to me yet again, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 8:6"}, "\u201cBecause this people has refused the waters of Shiloah that go softly, and rejoice in Rezin and Remaliah\u2019s son;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 8:7"}, "now therefore, behold, the Lord brings upon them the mighty flood waters of the River: the king of Assyria and all his\nglory. It will come up over all its channels, and go over all its banks.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 8:8"}, "It will sweep onward into Judah. It will overflow and pass through. It will reach even to the neck. The stretching out of\nits wings will fill the width of your land, Immanuel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 8:9"}, "Make an uproar, you peoples, and be broken in pieces! Listen, all you from far countries: dress for battle, and be\nshattered! Dress for battle, and be shattered! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 8:10"}, "Take counsel together, and it will be brought to nothing; speak the word, and it will not stand, for Allah is with us.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 8:11"}, "For the LORD spoke this to me with a strong hand, and instructed me not to walk in the way of this people, saying,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 8:12"}, "\u201cDon\u2019t say, \u2018A conspiracy!\u2019 concerning all about which this people say, \u2018A conspiracy!\u2019 neither fear their threats, nor\nbe terrorised. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 8:13"}, "The LORD of Armies is who you must respect as holy. He is the one you must fear. He is the one you must dread.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 8:14"}, "He will be a sanctuary, but for both houses of Israel, he will be a stumbling stone and a rock that makes them fall. For\nthe people of Jerusalem, he will be a trap and a snare. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 8:15"}, "Many will stumble over it, fall, be broken, be snared, and be captured.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 8:16"}, "Wrap up the covenant. Seal the law amongst my disciples. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 8:17"}, "I will wait for the LORD, who hides his face from the house of Yaqub, and I will look for him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 8:18"}, "Behold, I and the children whom the LORD has given me are for signs and for wonders in Israel from the LORD of Armies,\nwho dwells in Mount Zion. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 8:19"}, "When they tell you, \u201cConsult with those who have familiar spirits and with the wizards, who chirp and who mutter,\u201d\nshouldn\u2019t a people consult with their Allah? Should they consult the dead on behalf of the living?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 8:20"}, "Turn to the law and to the covenant! If they don\u2019t speak according to this word, surely there is no morning for them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 8:21"}, "They will pass through it, very distressed and hungry. It will happen that when they are hungry, they will worry, and\ncurse by their king and by their Allah. They will turn their faces upward,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 8:22"}, "and look to the earth, and see distress, darkness, and the gloom of anguish. They will be driven into thick darkness.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 9"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 9:1"}, "But there shall be no more gloom for her who was in anguish. In the former time, he brought into contempt the land of\nZebulun and the land of Naphtali; but in the latter time he has made it glorious, by the way of the sea, beyond the Jordan,\nGalilee of the nations. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 9:2"}, "The people who walked in darkness have seen a great light. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The light has shined on those who lived in the land of the shadow of death.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 9:3"}, "You have multiplied the nation. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You have increased their joy. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["They rejoice before you according to the joy in harvest, as men rejoice when they divide the plunder.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 9:4"}, "For the yoke of his burden, and the staff of his shoulder, the rod of his oppressor, you have broken as in the day of\nMidian. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 9:5"}, "For all the armour of the armed man in the noisy battle, and the garments rolled in blood, will be for burning, fuel for\nthe fire. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 9:6"}, "For a child is born to us. A son is given to us; and the government will be on his shoulders. His name will be called\nWonderful, Counsellor, Mighty Allah, Everlasting Father, Prince of Peace.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 9:7"}, "Of the increase of his government and of peace there shall be no end, on Dawood\u2019s throne, and on his kingdom, to establish\nit, and to uphold it with justice and with righteousness from that time on, even forever. The zeal of the LORD of Armies will\nperform this. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 9:8"}, "The Lord sent a word into Yaqub, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and it falls on Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 9:9"}, "All the people will know, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["including Ephraim and the inhabitants of Samaria, who say in pride and in arrogance of heart,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 9:10"}, "\u201cThe bricks have fallen, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but we will build with cut stone. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["The sycamore fig trees have been cut down, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but we will put cedars in their place.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 9:11"}, "Therefore the LORD will set up on high against him the adversaries of Rezin,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will stir up his enemies, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 9:12"}, "The Syrians in front, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the Philistines behind; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and they will devour Israel with open mouth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["For all this, his anger is not turned away, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but his hand is stretched out still. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 9:13"}, "Yet the people have not turned to him who struck them, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["neither have they sought the LORD of Armies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 9:14"}, "Therefore the LORD will cut off from Israel head and tail,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["palm branch and reed, in one day. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 9:15"}, "The elder and the honourable man is the head, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the prophet who teaches lies is the tail. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 9:16"}, "For those who lead this people lead them astray; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and those who are led by them are destroyed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 9:17"}, "Therefore the Lord will not rejoice over their young men, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["neither will he have compassion on their fatherless and widows;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for everyone is profane and an evildoer, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and every mouth speaks folly. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["For all this his anger is not turned away, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but his hand is stretched out still. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 9:18"}, "For wickedness burns like a fire. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["It devours the briers and thorns; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["yes, it kindles in the thickets of the forest, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and they roll upward in a column of smoke. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 9:19"}, "Through the LORD of Armies\u2019 wrath, the land is burnt up; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the people are the fuel for the fire. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["No one spares his brother. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 9:20"}, "One will devour on the right hand, and be hungry; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he will eat on the left hand, and they will not be satisfied.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Everyone will eat the flesh of his own arm: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 9:21"}, "Manasseh, Ephraim; and Ephraim, Manasseh; and they together shall be against Judah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["For all this his anger is not turned away, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but his hand is stretched out still. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 10"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 10:1"}, "Woe to those who decree unrighteous decrees, and to the writers who write oppressive decrees;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 10:2"}, "to deprive the needy from justice, and to rob the poor amongst my people of their rights, that widows may be their\nplunder, and that they may make the fatherless their prey! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 10:3"}, "What will you do in the day of visitation, and in the desolation which will come from afar? To whom will you flee for\nhelp? Where will you leave your wealth? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 10:4"}, "They will only bow down under the prisoners, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will fall under the slain. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["For all this his anger is not turned away, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but his hand is stretched out still. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 10:5"}, "Alas Assyrian, the rod of my anger, the staff in whose hand is my indignation!\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 10:6"}, "I will send him against a profane nation, and against the people who anger me I will give him a command to take the\nplunder and to take the prey, and to tread them down like the mire of the streets.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 10:7"}, "However he doesn\u2019t mean so, neither does his heart think so; but it is in his heart to destroy, and to cut off not a few\nnations. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 10:8"}, "For he says, \u201cAren\u2019t all of my princes kings? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 10:9"}, "Isn\u2019t Calno like Carchemish? Isn\u2019t Hamath like Arpad? Isn\u2019t Samaria like Damascus?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 10:10"}, "As my hand has found the kingdoms of the idols, whose engraved images exceeded those of Jerusalem and of Samaria;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 10:11"}, "shall I not, as I have done to Samaria and her idols, so do to Jerusalem and her idols?\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 10:12"}, "Therefore it will happen that when the Lord has performed his whole work on Mount Zion and on Jerusalem, I will punish\nthe fruit of the wilful proud heart of the king of Assyria, and the insolence of his arrogant looks.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 10:13"}, "For he has said, \u201cBy the strength of my hand I have done it, and by my wisdom; for I have understanding. I have removed\nthe boundaries of the peoples, and have robbed their treasures. Like a valiant man I have brought down their rulers.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 10:14"}, "My hand has found the riches of the peoples like a nest, and like one gathers eggs that are abandoned, I have gathered\nall the earth. There was no one who moved their wing, or that opened their mouth, or chirped.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 10:15"}, "Should an axe brag against him who chops with it? Should a saw exalt itself above him who saws with it? As if a rod\nshould lift those who lift it up, or as if a staff should lift up someone who is not wood.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 10:16"}, "Therefore the Lord, the LORD of Armies, will send amongst his fat ones leanness; and under his glory a burning will be\nkindled like the burning of fire. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 10:17"}, "The light of Israel will be for a fire, and his Holy One for a flame; and it will burn and devour his thorns and his\nbriers in one day. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 10:18"}, "He will consume the glory of his forest, and of his fruitful field, both soul and body. It will be as when a standard\nbearer faints. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 10:19"}, "The remnant of the trees of his forest shall be few, so that a child could write their number.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 10:20"}, "It will come to pass in that day that the remnant of Israel, and those who have escaped from the house of Yaqub will no\nmore again lean on him who struck them, but shall lean on the LORD, the Holy One of Israel, in truth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 10:21"}, "A remnant will return, even the remnant of Yaqub, to the mighty Allah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 10:22"}, "For though your people, Israel, are like the sand of the sea, only a remnant of them will return. A destruction is\ndetermined, overflowing with righteousness. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 10:23"}, "For the Lord, the LORD of Armies, will make a full end, and that determined, throughout all the earth.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 10:24"}, "Therefore the Lord, the LORD of Armies, says \u201cMy people who dwell in Zion, don\u2019t be afraid of the Assyrian, though he\nstrike you with the rod, and lift up his staff against you, as Egypt did.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ISA 10:25"}, "For yet a very little while, and the indignation against you will be accomplished, and my anger will be directed to his\ndestruction.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ISA 10:26"}, "The LORD of Armies will stir up a scourge against him, as in the slaughter of Midian at the rock of Oreb. His rod will be\nover the sea, and he will lift it up like he did against Egypt. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ISA 10:27"}, "It will happen in that day that his burden will depart from off your shoulder, and his yoke from off your neck, and the\nyoke shall be destroyed because of the anointing oil. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ISA 10:28"}, "He has come to Aiath. He has passed through Migron. At Michmash he stores his baggage.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ISA 10:29"}, "They have gone over the pass. They have taken up their lodging at Geba. Ramah trembles. Gibeah of Saul has fled.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ISA 10:30"}, "Cry aloud with your voice, daughter of Gallim! Listen, Laishah! You poor Anathoth!\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ISA 10:31"}, "Madmenah is a fugitive. The inhabitants of Gebim flee for safety.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ISA 10:32"}, "This very day he will halt at Nob. He shakes his hand at the mountain of the daughter of Zion, the hill of Jerusalem.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "ISA 10:33"}, "Behold, the Lord, the LORD of Armies, will lop the boughs with terror. The tall will be cut down, and the lofty will be\nbrought low. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "ISA 10:34"}, "He will cut down the thickets of the forest with iron, and Lebanon will fall by the Mighty One.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 11"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 11:1"}, "A shoot will come out of the stock of Jesse, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a branch out of his roots will bear fruit. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 11:2"}, "The LORD\u2019s Spirit will rest on him: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the spirit of wisdom and understanding, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the spirit of counsel and might, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the spirit of knowledge and of the fear of the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 11:3"}, "His delight will be in the fear of the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He will not judge by the sight of his eyes, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["neither decide by the hearing of his ears; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 11:4"}, "but he will judge the poor with righteousness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and decide with equity for the humble of the earth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He will strike the earth with the rod of his mouth; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and with the breath of his lips he will kill the wicked. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 11:5"}, "Righteousness will be the belt of his waist, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and faithfulness the belt of his waist. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 11:6"}, "The wolf will live with the lamb, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the leopard will lie down with the young goat, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the calf, the young lion, and the fattened calf together; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a little child will lead them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 11:7"}, "The cow and the bear will graze. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Their young ones will lie down together. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The lion will eat straw like the ox. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 11:8"}, "The nursing child will play near a cobra\u2019s hole, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the weaned child will put his hand on the viper\u2019s den. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 11:9"}, "They will not hurt nor destroy in all my holy mountain; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for the earth will be full of the knowledge of the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["as the waters cover the sea. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 11:10"}, "It will happen in that day that the nations will seek the root of Jesse, who stands as a banner of the peoples; and his\nresting place will be glorious. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 11:11"}, "It will happen in that day that the Lord will set his hand again the second time to recover the remnant that is left of\nhis people from Assyria, from Egypt, from Pathros, from Cush, from Elam, from Shinar, from Hamath, and from the islands of the\nsea. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 11:12"}, "He will set up a banner for the nations, and will assemble the outcasts of Israel, and gather together the dispersed of\nJudah from the four corners of the earth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 11:13"}, "The envy also of Ephraim will depart, and those who persecute Judah will be cut off. Ephraim won\u2019t envy Judah, and Judah\nwon\u2019t persecute Ephraim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 11:14"}, "They will fly down on the shoulders of the Philistines on the west. Together they will plunder the children of the east.\nThey will extend their power over Edom and Moab, and the children of Ammon will obey them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 11:15"}, "The LORD will utterly destroy the tongue of the Egyptian sea; and with his scorching wind he will wave his hand over the\nRiver, and will split it into seven streams, and cause men to march over in sandals.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 11:16"}, "There will be a highway for the remnant that is left of his people from Assyria, like there was for Israel in the day\nthat he came up out of the land of Egypt. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 12"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 12:1"}, "In that day you will say, \u201cI will give thanks to you, the LORD; for though you were angry with me, your anger has turned\naway and you comfort me. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 12:2"}, "Behold, Allah is my salvation. I will trust, and will not be afraid; for the LORD, the LORD, is my strength and song; and\nhe has become my salvation.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 12:3"}, "Therefore with joy you will draw water out of the wells of salvation.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 12:4"}, "In that day you will say, \u201cGive thanks to the LORD! Call on his name. Declare his doings amongst the peoples. Proclaim\nthat his name is exalted! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 12:5"}, "Sing to the LORD, for he has done excellent things! Let this be known in all the earth!\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 12:6"}, "Cry aloud and shout, you inhabitant of Zion; for the Holy One of Israel is great amongst you!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 13"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 13:1"}, "The burden of Babylon, which Isaiah the son of Amoz saw. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 13:2"}, "Set up a banner on the bare mountain! Lift up your voice to them! Wave your hand, that they may go into the gates of the\nnobles. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 13:3"}, "I have commanded my consecrated ones; yes, I have called my mighty men for my anger, even my proudly exulting ones.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 13:4"}, "The noise of a multitude is in the mountains, as of a great people; the noise of an uproar of the kingdoms of the nations\ngathered together! The LORD of Armies is mustering the army for the battle.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 13:5"}, "They come from a far country, from the uttermost part of heaven, even the LORD, and the weapons of his indignation, to\ndestroy the whole land. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 13:6"}, "Wail, for the LORD\u2019s day is at hand! It will come as destruction from the Almighty.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 13:7"}, "Therefore all hands will be feeble, and everyone\u2019s heart will melt.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 13:8"}, "They will be dismayed. Pangs and sorrows will seize them. They will be in pain like a woman in labour. They will look in\namazement one at another. Their faces will be faces of flame. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 13:9"}, "Behold, the day of the LORD comes, cruel, with wrath and fierce anger; to make the land a desolation, and to destroy its\nsinners out of it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 13:10"}, "For the stars of the sky and its constellations will not give their light. The sun will be darkened in its going out, and\nthe moon will not cause its light to shine. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 13:11"}, "I will punish the world for their evil, and the wicked for their iniquity. I will cause the arrogance of the proud to\ncease, and will humble the arrogance of the terrible. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 13:12"}, "I will make people more rare than fine gold, even a person than the pure gold of Ophir.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 13:13"}, "Therefore I will make the heavens tremble, and the earth will be shaken out of its place in the LORD of Armies\u2019 wrath,\nand in the day of his fierce anger. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 13:14"}, "It will happen that like a hunted gazelle, and like sheep that no one gathers, they will each turn to their own people,\nand will each flee to their own land. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 13:15"}, "Everyone who is found will be thrust through. Everyone who is captured will fall by the sword.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 13:16"}, "Their infants also will be dashed in pieces before their eyes. Their houses will be ransacked, and their wives raped.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 13:17"}, "Behold, I will stir up the Medes against them, who will not value silver, and as for gold, they will not delight in it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 13:18"}, "Their bows will dash the young men in pieces; and they shall have no pity on the fruit of the womb. Their eyes will not\nspare children. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 13:19"}, "Babylon, the glory of kingdoms, the beauty of the Chaldeans\u2019 pride, will be like when Allah overthrew Sodom and Gomorrah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 13:20"}, "It will never be inhabited, neither will it be lived in from generation to generation. The Arabian will not pitch a tent\nthere, neither will shepherds make their flocks lie down there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 13:21"}, "But wild animals of the desert will lie there, and their houses will be full of jackals. Ostriches will dwell there, and\nwild goats will frolic there. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 13:22"}, "Wolves will cry in their fortresses, and jackals in the pleasant palaces. Her time is near to come, and her days will not\nbe prolonged. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 14"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 14:1"}, "For the LORD will have compassion on Yaqub, and will yet choose Israel, and set them in their own land. The foreigner will\njoin himself with them, and they will unite with the house of Yaqub.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 14:2"}, "The peoples will take them, and bring them to their place. The house of Israel will possess them in the LORD\u2019s land for\nservants and for handmaids. They will take as captives those whose captives they were; and they shall rule over their\noppressors. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 14:3"}, "It will happen in the day that the LORD will give you rest from your sorrow, from your trouble, and from the hard service\nin which you were made to serve, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 14:4"}, "that you will take up this parable against the king of Babylon, and say, \u201cHow the oppressor has ceased! The golden city\nhas ceased!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 14:5"}, "The LORD has broken the staff of the wicked, the sceptre of the rulers,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 14:6"}, "who struck the peoples in wrath with a continual stroke, who ruled the nations in anger, with a persecution that no one\nrestrained. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 14:7"}, "The whole earth is at rest, and is quiet. They break out in song.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 14:8"}, "Yes, the cypress trees rejoice with you, with the cedars of Lebanon, saying, \u201cSince you are humbled, no lumberjack has\ncome up against us.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 14:9"}, "Sheol", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["14:9 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Sheol is the place of the dead."]}], "caller": "+"}, " from beneath has moved for you to meet you at your coming. It\nstirs up the departed spirits for you, even all the rulers of the earth. It has raised up from their thrones all the kings of\nthe nations. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 14:10"}, "They all will answer and ask you, \u201cHave you also become as weak as we are? Have you become like us?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 14:11"}, "Your pomp is brought down to Sheol,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["14:11 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Sheol is the place of the dead.\n"]}], "caller": "+"}, " with the sound of your stringed instruments. Maggots are spread out under you, and worms cover you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 14:12"}, "How you have fallen from heaven, shining one, son of the dawn! How you are cut down to the ground, who laid the nations\nlow! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 14:13"}, "You said in your heart, \u201cI will ascend into heaven! I will exalt my throne above the stars of Allah! I will sit on the\nmountain of assembly, in the far north! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 14:14"}, "I will ascend above the heights of the clouds! I will make myself like the Most High!\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 14:15"}, "Yet you shall be brought down to Sheol,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["14:15 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Sheol is the place of the\ndead."]}], "caller": "+"}, " to the depths of the pit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 14:16"}, "Those who see you will stare at you. They will ponder you, saying, \u201cIs this the man who made the earth to tremble, who\nshook kingdoms, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 14:17"}, "who made the world like a wilderness, and overthrew its cities, who didn\u2019t release his prisoners to their home?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 14:18"}, "All the kings of the nations, sleep in glory, everyone in his own house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 14:19"}, "But you are cast away from your tomb like an abominable branch, clothed with the slain, who are thrust through with the\nsword, who go down to the stones of the pit; like a dead body trodden under foot.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 14:20"}, "You will not join them in burial, because you have destroyed your land. You have killed your people. The offspring of\nevildoers will not be named forever. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 14:21"}, "Prepare for slaughter of his children because of the iniquity of their fathers, that they not rise up and possess the\nearth, and fill the surface of the world with cities. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 14:22"}, "\u201cI will rise up against them,\u201d says the LORD of Armies, \u201cand cut off from Babylon name and remnant, and son and son\u2019s\nson,\u201d says the LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 14:23"}, "\u201cI will also make it a possession for the porcupine, and pools of water. I will sweep it with the broom of destruction,\u201d\nsays the LORD of Armies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 14:24"}, "The LORD of Armies has sworn, saying, \u201cSurely, as I have thought, so shall it happen; and as I have purposed, so shall it\nstand: \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ISA 14:25"}, "that I will break the Assyrian in my land, and tread him under foot on my mountains. Then his yoke will leave them, and\nhis burden leave their shoulders. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ISA 14:26"}, "This is the plan that is determined for the whole earth. This is the hand that is stretched out over all the nations.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ISA 14:27"}, "For the LORD of Armies has planned, and who can stop it? His hand is stretched out, and who can turn it back?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ISA 14:28"}, "This burden was in the year that king Ahaz died. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ISA 14:29"}, "Don\u2019t rejoice, O Philistia, all of you, because the rod that struck you is broken; for out of the serpent\u2019s root an adder\nwill emerge, and his fruit will be a fiery flying serpent. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ISA 14:30"}, "The firstborn of the poor will eat, and the needy will lie down in safety; and I will kill your root with famine, and\nyour remnant will be killed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ISA 14:31"}, "Howl, gate! Cry, city! You are melted away, Philistia, all of you; for smoke comes out of the north, and there is no\nstraggler in his ranks. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ISA 14:32"}, "What will they answer the messengers of the nation? That the LORD has founded Zion, and in her the afflicted of his\npeople will take refuge. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 15"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 15:1"}, "The burden of Moab. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["For in a night, Ar of Moab is laid waste, and brought to nothing. For in a night Kir of Moab is laid waste, and brought to\nnothing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 15:2"}, "They have gone up to Bayith, and to Dibon, to the high places, to weep. Moab wails over Nebo and over Medeba. Baldness is\non all of their heads. Every beard is cut off. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 15:3"}, "In their streets, they clothe themselves in sackcloth. In their streets and on their housetops, everyone wails, weeping\nabundantly. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 15:4"}, "Heshbon cries out with Elealeh. Their voice is heard even to Jahaz. Therefore the armed men of Moab cry aloud. Their souls\ntremble within them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 15:5"}, "My heart cries out for Moab! Her nobles flee to Zoar, to Eglath Shelishiyah; for they go up by the ascent of Luhith with\nweeping; for on the way to Horonaim, they raise up a cry of destruction.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 15:6"}, "For the waters of Nimrim will be desolate; for the grass has withered away, the tender grass fails, there is no green\nthing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 15:7"}, "Therefore they will carry away the abundance they have gotten, and that which they have stored up, over the brook of the\nwillows. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 15:8"}, "For the cry has gone around the borders of Moab, its wailing to Eglaim, and its wailing to Beer Elim.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 15:9"}, "For the waters of Dimon are full of blood; for I will bring yet more on Dimon, a lion on those of Moab who escape, and on\nthe remnant of the land. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 16"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 16:1"}, "Send the lambs for the ruler of the land from Selah to the wilderness, to the mountain of the daughter of Zion.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 16:2"}, "For it will be that as wandering birds, as a scattered nest, so will the daughters of Moab be at the fords of the Arnon.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 16:3"}, "Give counsel! Execute justice! Make your shade like the night in the middle of the noonday! Hide the outcasts! Don\u2019t\nbetray the fugitive! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 16:4"}, "Let my outcasts dwell with you! As for Moab, be a hiding place for him from the face of the destroyer. For the\nextortionist is brought to nothing. Destruction ceases. The oppressors are consumed out of the land.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 16:5"}, "A throne will be established in loving kindness. One will sit on it in truth, in the tent of Dawood, judging, seeking\njustice, and swift to do righteousness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 16:6"}, "We have heard of the pride of Moab, that he is very proud; even of his arrogance, his pride, and his wrath. His boastings\nare nothing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 16:7"}, "Therefore Moab will wail for Moab. Everyone will wail. You will mourn for the raisin cakes of Kir Hareseth, utterly\nstricken. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 16:8"}, "For the fields of Heshbon languish with the vine of Sibmah. The lords of the nations have broken down its choice branches,\nwhich reached even to Jazer, which wandered into the wilderness. Its shoots were spread abroad. They passed over the sea.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 16:9"}, "Therefore I will weep with the weeping of Jazer for the vine of Sibmah. I will water you with my tears, Heshbon, and\nElealeh: for on your summer fruits and on your harvest the battle shout has fallen.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 16:10"}, "Gladness is taken away, and joy out of the fruitful field; and in the vineyards there will be no singing, neither joyful\nnoise. Nobody will tread out wine in the presses. I have made the shouting stop.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 16:11"}, "Therefore my heart sounds like a harp for Moab, and my inward parts for Kir Heres.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 16:12"}, "It will happen that when Moab presents himself, when he wearies himself on the high place, and comes to his sanctuary to\npray, that he will not prevail. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 16:13"}, "This is the word that the LORD spoke concerning Moab in time past.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 16:14"}, "But now the LORD has spoken, saying, \u201cWithin three years, as a worker bound by contract would count them, the glory of\nMoab shall be brought into contempt, with all his great multitude; and the remnant will be very small and feeble.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 17"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 17:1"}, "The burden of Damascus. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["\u201cBehold, Damascus is taken away from being a city, and it will be a ruinous heap.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 17:2"}, "The cities of Aroer are forsaken. They will be for flocks, which shall lie down, and no one shall make them afraid.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 17:3"}, "The fortress shall cease from Ephraim, and the kingdom from Damascus, and the remnant of Syria. They will be as the glory\nof the children of Israel,\u201d says the LORD of Armies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 17:4"}, "\u201cIt will happen in that day that the glory of Yaqub will be made thin, and the fatness of his flesh will become lean.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 17:5"}, "It will be like when the harvester gathers the wheat, and his arm reaps the grain. Yes, it will be like when one gleans\ngrain in the valley of Rephaim. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 17:6"}, "Yet gleanings will be left there, like the shaking of an olive tree, two or three olives in the top of the uppermost\nbough, four or five in the outermost branches of a fruitful tree,\u201d says the LORD, Allah of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 17:7"}, "In that day, people will look to their Maker, and their eyes will have respect for the Holy One of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 17:8"}, "They will not look to the altars, the work of their hands; neither shall they respect that which their fingers have made,\neither the Asherah poles, or the incense altars. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 17:9"}, "In that day, their strong cities will be like the forsaken places in the woods and on the mountain top, which were\nforsaken from before the children of Israel; and it will be a desolation.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 17:10"}, "For you have forgotten Allah of your salvation, and have not remembered the rock of your strength. Therefore you plant\npleasant plants, and set out foreign seedlings. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 17:11"}, "In the day of your planting, you hedge it in. In the morning, you make your seed blossom, but the harvest flees away in\nthe day of grief and of desperate sorrow. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 17:12"}, "Ah, the uproar of many peoples, who roar like the roaring of the seas; and the rushing of nations, that rush like the\nrushing of mighty waters! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 17:13"}, "The nations will rush like the rushing of many waters: but he will rebuke them, and they will flee far off, and will be\nchased like the chaff of the mountains before the wind, and like the whirling dust before the storm.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 17:14"}, "At evening, behold, terror! Before the morning, they are no more. This is the portion of those who plunder us, and the\nlot of those who rob us. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 18"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 18:1"}, "Ah, the land of the rustling of wings, which is beyond the rivers of Ethiopia;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 18:2"}, "that sends ambassadors by the sea, even in vessels of papyrus on the waters, saying, \u201cGo, you swift messengers, to a\nnation tall and smooth, to a people awesome from their beginning onward, a nation that measures out and treads down, whose land\nthe rivers divide!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 18:3"}, "All you inhabitants of the world, and you dwellers on the earth, when a banner is lifted up on the mountains, look! When\nthe trumpet is blown, listen! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 18:4"}, "For the LORD said to me, \u201cI will be still, and I will see in my dwelling place, like clear heat in sunshine, like a cloud\nof dew in the heat of harvest.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 18:5"}, "For before the harvest, when the blossom is over, and the flower becomes a ripening grape, he will cut off the sprigs with\npruning hooks, and he will cut down and take away the spreading branches.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 18:6"}, "They will be left together for the ravenous birds of the mountains, and for the animals of the earth. The ravenous birds\nwill eat them in the summer, and all the animals of the earth will eat them in the winter.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 18:7"}, "In that time, a present will be brought to the LORD of Armies from a people tall and smooth, even from a people awesome\nfrom their beginning onward, a nation that measures out and treads down, whose land the rivers divide, to the place of the name\nof the LORD of Armies, Mount Zion. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 19"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 19:1"}, "The burden of Egypt. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["\u201cBehold, the LORD rides on a swift cloud, and comes to Egypt. The idols of Egypt will tremble at his presence; and the heart\nof Egypt will melt within it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 19:2"}, "I will stir up the Egyptians against the Egyptians, and they will fight everyone against his brother, and everyone against\nhis neighbour; city against city, and kingdom against kingdom. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 19:3"}, "The spirit of Egypt will fail within it. I will destroy its counsel. They will seek the idols, the charmers, those who\nhave familiar spirits, and the wizards. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 19:4"}, "I will give over the Egyptians into the hand of a cruel lord. A fierce king will rule over them,\u201d says the Lord, the LORD\nof Armies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 19:5"}, "The waters will fail from the sea, and the river will be wasted and become dry.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 19:6"}, "The rivers will become foul. The streams of Egypt will be diminished and dried up. The reeds and flags will wither away.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 19:7"}, "The meadows by the Nile, by the brink of the Nile, and all the sown fields of the Nile, will become dry, be driven away,\nand be no more. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 19:8"}, "The fishermen will lament, and all those who fish in the Nile will mourn, and those who spread nets on the waters will\nlanguish. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 19:9"}, "Moreover those who work in combed flax, and those who weave white cloth, will be confounded.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 19:10"}, "The pillars will be broken in pieces. All those who work for hire will be grieved in soul.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 19:11"}, "The princes of Zoan are utterly foolish. The counsel of the wisest counsellors of Pharaoh has become stupid. How do you\nsay to Pharaoh, \u201cI am the son of the wise, the son of ancient kings?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 19:12"}, "Where then are your wise men? Let them tell you now; and let them know what the LORD of Armies has purposed concerning\nEgypt. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 19:13"}, "The princes of Zoan have become fools. The princes of Memphis are deceived. They have caused Egypt to go astray, who are\nthe cornerstone of her tribes. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 19:14"}, "The LORD has mixed a spirit of perverseness in the middle of her; and they have caused Egypt to go astray in all of its\nworks, like a drunken man staggers in his vomit. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 19:15"}, "Neither shall there be any work for Egypt, which head or tail, palm branch or rush, may do.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 19:16"}, "In that day the Egyptians will be like women. They will tremble and fear because of the shaking of the LORD of Armies\u2019s\nhand, which he shakes over them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 19:17"}, "The land of Judah will become a terror to Egypt. Everyone to whom mention is made of it will be afraid, because of the\nplans of the LORD of Armies, which he determines against it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 19:18"}, "In that day, there will be five cities in the land of Egypt that speak the language of Canaan, and swear to the LORD of\nArmies. One will be called \u201cThe city of destruction.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 19:19"}, "In that day, there will be an altar to the LORD in the middle of the land of Egypt, and a pillar to the LORD at its\nborder. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 19:20"}, "It will be for a sign and for a witness to the LORD of Armies in the land of Egypt; for they will cry to the LORD because\nof oppressors, and he will send them a saviour and a defender, and he will deliver them.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 19:21"}, "The LORD will be known to Egypt, and the Egyptians will know the LORD in that day. Yes, they will worship with sacrifice\nand offering, and will vow a vow to the LORD, and will perform it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 19:22"}, "The LORD will strike Egypt, striking and healing. They will return to the LORD, and he will be entreated by them, and\nwill heal them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 19:23"}, "In that day there will be a highway out of Egypt to Assyria, and the Assyrian shall come into Egypt, and the Egyptian\ninto Assyria; and the Egyptians will worship with the Assyrians.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 19:24"}, "In that day, Israel will be the third with Egypt and with Assyria, a blessing within the earth;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ISA 19:25"}, "because the LORD of Armies has blessed them, saying, \u201cBlessed be Egypt my people, Assyria the work of my hands, and\nIsrael my inheritance.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 20"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 20:1"}, "In the year that Tartan came to Ashdod, when Sargon the king of Assyria sent him, and he fought against Ashdod and took\nit; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 20:2"}, "at that time the LORD spoke by Isaiah the son of Amoz, saying, \u201cGo, and loosen the sackcloth from off your waist, and take\nyour sandals from off your feet.\u201d He did so, walking naked and barefoot.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 20:3"}, "The LORD said, \u201cAs my servant Isaiah has walked naked and barefoot three years for a sign and a wonder concerning Egypt\nand concerning Ethiopia, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 20:4"}, "so the king of Assyria will lead away the captives of Egypt and the exiles of Ethiopia, young and old, naked and barefoot,\nand with buttocks uncovered, to the shame of Egypt. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 20:5"}, "They will be dismayed and confounded, because of Ethiopia their expectation, and of Egypt their glory.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 20:6"}, "The inhabitants of this coast land will say in that day, \u2018Behold, this is our expectation, where we fled for help to be\ndelivered from the king of Assyria. And we, how will we escape?\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 21"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 21:1"}, "The burden of the wilderness of the sea. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["As whirlwinds in the South sweep through, it comes from the wilderness, from an awesome land.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 21:2"}, "A grievous vision is declared to me. The treacherous man deals treacherously, and the destroyer destroys. Go up, Elam;\nattack! I have stopped all of Media\u2019s sighing. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 21:3"}, "Therefore my thighs are filled with anguish. Pains have seized me, like the pains of a woman in labour. I am in so much\npain that I can\u2019t hear. I so am dismayed that I can\u2019t see. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 21:4"}, "My heart flutters. Horror has frightened me. The twilight that I desired has been turned into trembling for me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 21:5"}, "They prepare the table. They set the watch. They eat. They drink. Rise up, you princes, oil the shield!\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 21:6"}, "For the Lord said to me, \u201cGo, set a watchman. Let him declare what he sees.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 21:7"}, "When he sees a troop, horsemen in pairs, a troop of donkeys, a troop of camels, he shall listen diligently with great\nattentiveness.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 21:8"}, "He cried like a lion: \u201cLord, I stand continually on the watchtower in the daytime, and every night I stay at my post.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 21:9"}, "Behold, here comes a troop of men, horsemen in pairs.\u201d He answered, \u201cFallen, fallen is Babylon; and all the engraved\nimages of her gods are broken to the ground. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 21:10"}, "You are my threshing, and the grain of my floor!\u201d That which I have heard from the LORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, I\nhave declared to you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 21:11"}, "The burden of Dumah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["One calls to me out of Seir, \u201cWatchman, what of the night? Watchman, what of the night?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 21:12"}, "The watchman said, \u201cThe morning comes, and also the night. If you will enquire, enquire. Come back again.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 21:13"}, "The burden on Arabia. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["In the forest in Arabia you will lodge, you caravans of Dedanites.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 21:14"}, "They brought water to him who was thirsty. The inhabitants of the land of Tema met the fugitives with their bread.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 21:15"}, "For they fled away from the swords, from the drawn sword, from the bent bow, and from the heat of battle.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 21:16"}, "For the Lord said to me, \u201cWithin a year, as a worker bound by contract would count it, all the glory of Kedar will fail,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 21:17"}, "and the residue of the number of the archers, the mighty men of the children of Kedar, will be few; for the LORD, Allah\nof Israel, has spoken it.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 22"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 22:1"}, "The burden of the valley of vision. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["What ails you now, that you have all gone up to the housetops?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 22:2"}, "You that are full of shouting, a tumultuous city, a joyous town; your slain are not slain with the sword, neither are they\ndead in battle. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 22:3"}, "All your rulers fled away together. They were bound by the archers. All who were found by you were bound together. They\nfled far away. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 22:4"}, "Therefore I said, \u201cLook away from me. I will weep bitterly. Don\u2019t labour to comfort me for the destruction of the daughter\nof my people. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 22:5"}, "For it is a day of confusion, and of treading down, and of perplexity, from the Lord, the LORD of Armies, in the valley of\nvision, a breaking down of the walls, and a crying to the mountains.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 22:6"}, "Elam carried his quiver, with chariots of men and horsemen; and Kir uncovered the shield.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 22:7"}, "Your choicest valleys were full of chariots, and the horsemen set themselves in array at the gate.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 22:8"}, "He took away the covering of Judah; and you looked in that day to the armour in the house of the forest.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 22:9"}, "You saw the breaches of Dawood\u2019s city, that they were many; and you gathered together the waters of the lower pool.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 22:10"}, "You counted the houses of Jerusalem, and you broke down the houses to fortify the wall.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 22:11"}, "You also made a reservoir between the two walls for the water of the old pool. But you didn\u2019t look to him who had done\nthis, neither did you have respect for him who planed it long ago.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 22:12"}, "In that day, the Lord, the LORD of Armies, called to weeping, to mourning, to baldness, and to dressing in sackcloth;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 22:13"}, "and behold, joy and gladness, killing cattle and killing sheep, eating meat and drinking wine: \u201cLet\u2019s eat and drink, for\ntomorrow we will die.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 22:14"}, "The LORD of Armies revealed himself in my ears, \u201cSurely this iniquity will not be forgiven you until you die,\u201d says the\nLord, the LORD of Armies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 22:15"}, "The Lord, the LORD of Armies says, \u201cGo, get yourself to this treasurer, even to Shebna, who is over the house, and say,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 22:16"}, "\u2018What are you doing here? Who has you here, that you have dug out a tomb here?\u2019 Cutting himself out a tomb on high,\nchiselling a habitation for himself in the rock!\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 22:17"}, "Behold, the LORD will overcome you and hurl you away violently. Yes, he will grasp you firmly.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 22:18"}, "He will surely wind you around and around, and throw you like a ball into a large country. There you will die, and there\nthe chariots of your glory will be, you shame of your lord\u2019s house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 22:19"}, "I will thrust you from your office. You will be pulled down from your station.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 22:20"}, "It will happen in that day that I will call my servant Eliakim the son of Hilkiah,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 22:21"}, "and I will clothe him with your robe, and strengthen him with your belt. I will commit your government into his hand; and\nhe will be a father to the inhabitants of Jerusalem, and to the house of Judah.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 22:22"}, "I will lay the key of Dawood\u2019s house on his shoulder. He will open, and no one will shut. He will shut, and no one will\nopen. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 22:23"}, "I will fasten him like a nail in a sure place. He will be for a throne of glory to his father\u2019s house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 22:24"}, "They will hang on him all the glory of his father\u2019s house, the offspring and the issue, every small vessel, from the cups\neven to all the pitchers. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ISA 22:25"}, "\u201cIn that day,\u201d says the LORD of Armies, \u201cthe nail that was fastened in a sure place will give way. It will be cut down\nand fall. The burden that was on it will be cut off, for the LORD has spoken it.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 23"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 23:1"}, "The burden of Tyre. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Howl, you ships of Tarshish! For it is laid waste, so that there is no house, no entering in. From the land of Kittim it is\nrevealed to them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 23:2"}, "Be still, you inhabitants of the coast, you whom the merchants of Sidon that pass over the sea, have replenished.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 23:3"}, "On great waters, the seed of the Shihor, the harvest of the Nile, was her revenue. She was the market of nations.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 23:4"}, "Be ashamed, Sidon; for the sea has spoken, the stronghold of the sea, saying, \u201cI have not travailed, nor given birth,\nneither have I nourished young men, nor brought up virgins.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 23:5"}, "When the report comes to Egypt, they will be in anguish at the report of Tyre.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 23:6"}, "Pass over to Tarshish! Wail, you inhabitants of the coast! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 23:7"}, "Is this your joyous city, whose antiquity is of ancient days, whose feet carried her far away to travel?\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 23:8"}, "Who has planned this against Tyre, the giver of crowns, whose merchants are princes, whose traders are the honourable of\nthe earth? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 23:9"}, "The LORD of Armies has planned it, to stain the pride of all glory, to bring into contempt all the honourable of the\nearth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 23:10"}, "Pass through your land like the Nile, daughter of Tarshish. There is no restraint any more.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 23:11"}, "He has stretched out his hand over the sea. He has shaken the kingdoms. The LORD has ordered the destruction of Canaan\u2019s\nstrongholds. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 23:12"}, "He said, \u201cYou shall rejoice no more, you oppressed virgin daughter of Sidon. Arise, pass over to Kittim. Even there you\nwill have no rest.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 23:13"}, "Behold, the land of the Chaldeans. This people didn\u2019t exist. The Assyrians founded it for those who dwell in the\nwilderness. They set up their towers. They overthrew its palaces. They made it a ruin.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 23:14"}, "Howl, you ships of Tarshish, for your stronghold is laid waste!\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 23:15"}, "It will come to pass in that day that Tyre will be forgotten seventy years, according to the days of one king. After the\nend of seventy years it will be to Tyre like in the song of the prostitute.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 23:16"}, "Take a harp; go about the city, you prostitute that has been forgotten. Make sweet melody. Sing many songs, that you may\nbe remembered. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 23:17"}, "It will happen after the end of seventy years that the LORD will visit Tyre. She will return to her wages, and will play\nthe prostitute with all the kingdoms of the world on the surface of the earth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 23:18"}, "Her merchandise and her wages will be holiness to the LORD. It will not be treasured nor laid up; for her merchandise\nwill be for those who dwell before the LORD, to eat sufficiently, and for durable clothing.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 24"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 24:1"}, "Behold, the LORD makes the earth empty, makes it waste, turns it upside down, and scatters its inhabitants.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 24:2"}, "It will be as with the people, so with the priest; as with the servant, so with his master; as with the maid, so with her\nmistress; as with the buyer, so with the seller; as with the creditor, so with the debtor; as with the taker of interest, so\nwith the giver of interest. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 24:3"}, "The earth will be utterly emptied and utterly laid waste; for the LORD has spoken this word.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 24:4"}, "The earth mourns and fades away. The world languishes and fades away. The lofty people of the earth languish.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 24:5"}, "The earth also is polluted under its inhabitants, because they have transgressed the laws, violated the statutes, and\nbroken the everlasting covenant. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 24:6"}, "Therefore the curse has devoured the earth, and those who dwell therein are found guilty. Therefore the inhabitants of the\nearth are burnt, and few men are left. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 24:7"}, "The new wine mourns. The vine languishes. All the merry-hearted sigh.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 24:8"}, "The mirth of tambourines ceases. The sound of those who rejoice ends. The joy of the harp ceases.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 24:9"}, "They will not drink wine with a song. Strong drink will be bitter to those who drink it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 24:10"}, "The confused city is broken down. Every house is shut up, that no man may come in.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 24:11"}, "There is a crying in the streets because of the wine. All joy is darkened. The mirth of the land is gone.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 24:12"}, "The city is left in desolation, and the gate is struck with destruction.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 24:13"}, "For it will be so within the earth amongst the peoples, as the shaking of an olive tree, as the gleanings when the\nvintage is done. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 24:14"}, "These shall lift up their voice. They will shout for the majesty of the LORD. They cry aloud from the sea.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 24:15"}, "Therefore glorify the LORD in the east, even the name of the LORD, Allah of Israel, in the islands of the sea!\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 24:16"}, "From the uttermost part of the earth have we heard songs. Glory to the righteous!\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["But I said, \u201cI pine away! I pine away! woe is me!\u201d The treacherous have dealt treacherously. Yes, the treacherous have dealt\nvery treacherously. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 24:17"}, "Fear, the pit, and the snare, are on you who inhabit the earth.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 24:18"}, "It will happen that he who flees from the noise of the fear will fall into the pit; and he who comes up out of the middle\nof the pit will be taken in the snare; for the windows on high are opened, and the foundations of the earth tremble.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 24:19"}, "The earth is utterly broken. The earth is torn apart. The earth is shaken violently.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 24:20"}, "The earth will stagger like a drunken man, and will sway back and forth like a hammock. Its disobedience will be heavy on\nit, and it will fall and not rise again. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 24:21"}, "It will happen in that day that the LORD will punish the army of the high ones on high, and the kings of the earth on the\nearth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 24:22"}, "They will be gathered together, as prisoners are gathered in the pit, and will be shut up in the prison; and after many\ndays they will be visited. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 24:23"}, "Then the moon will be confounded, and the sun ashamed; for the LORD of Armies will reign on Mount Zion, and in Jerusalem;\nand glory will be before his elders. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "25", "sid": "ISA 25"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 25:1"}, "The LORD, you are my Allah. I will exalt you! I will praise your name, for you have done wonderful things, things planned\nlong ago, in complete faithfulness and truth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 25:2"}, "For you have made a city into a heap, a fortified city into a ruin, a palace of strangers to be no city. It will never be\nbuilt. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 25:3"}, "Therefore a strong people will glorify you. A city of awesome nations will fear you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 25:4"}, "For you have been a stronghold to the poor, a stronghold to the needy in his distress, a refuge from the storm, a shade\nfrom the heat, when the blast of the dreaded ones is like a storm against the wall.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 25:5"}, "As the heat in a dry place you will bring down the noise of strangers; as the heat by the shade of a cloud, the song of\nthe dreaded ones will be brought low. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 25:6"}, "In this mountain, the LORD of Armies will make all peoples a feast of choice\nmeat,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["25:6 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["literally, fat things"]}], "caller": "+"}, " a feast of choice wines, of choice meat full of marrow, of well refined choice\nwines. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 25:7"}, "He will destroy in this mountain the surface of the covering that covers all peoples, and the veil that is spread over all\nnations. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 25:8"}, "He has swallowed up death forever! The Lord ALLAH will wipe away tears from off all faces. He will take the reproach of\nhis people away from off all the earth, for the LORD has spoken it.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 25:9"}, "It shall be said in that day, \u201cBehold, this is our Allah! We have waited for him, and he will save us! This is the LORD!\nWe have waited for him. We will be glad and rejoice in his salvation!\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 25:10"}, "For the LORD\u2019s hand will rest in this mountain. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Moab will be trodden down in his place, even like straw is trodden down in the water of the dunghill.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 25:11"}, "He will spread out his hands in the middle of it, like one who swims spreads out hands to swim, but his pride will be\nhumbled together with the craft of his hands. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 25:12"}, "He has brought the high fortress of your walls down, laid low, and brought to the ground, even to the dust.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "26", "sid": "ISA 26"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 26:1"}, "In that day, this song will be sung in the land of Judah: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cWe have a strong city. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Allah appoints salvation for walls and bulwarks. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 26:2"}, "Open the gates, that the righteous nation may enter: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the one which keeps faith. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 26:3"}, "You will keep whoever\u2019s mind is steadfast in perfect peace,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["because he trusts in you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 26:4"}, "Trust in the LORD forever; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for in the LORD, the LORD, is an everlasting Rock. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 26:5"}, "For he has brought down those who dwell on high, the lofty city.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He lays it low. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He lays it low even to the ground. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He brings it even to the dust. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 26:6"}, "The foot shall tread it down, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["even the feet of the poor \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the steps of the needy.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 26:7"}, "The way of the just is uprightness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You who are upright make the path of the righteous level. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 26:8"}, "Yes, in the way of your judgements, the LORD, we have waited for you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Your name and your renown are the desire of our soul. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 26:9"}, "With my soul I have desired you in the night. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, with my spirit within me I will seek you earnestly; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for when your judgements are in the earth, the inhabitants of the world learn righteousness.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 26:10"}, "Let favour be shown to the wicked, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["yet he will not learn righteousness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["In the land of uprightness he will deal wrongfully, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will not see the LORD\u2019s majesty. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 26:11"}, "The LORD, your hand is lifted up, yet they don\u2019t see; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but they will see your zeal for the people, and be disappointed.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, fire will consume your adversaries. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 26:12"}, "The LORD, you will ordain peace for us, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for you have also done all our work for us. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 26:13"}, "The LORD our Allah, other lords besides you have had dominion over us,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but we will only acknowledge your name. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 26:14"}, "The dead shall not live. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The departed spirits shall not rise. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Therefore you have visited and destroyed them, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and caused all memory of them to perish. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 26:15"}, "You have increased the nation, O LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You have increased the nation! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["You are glorified! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You have enlarged all the borders of the land. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 26:16"}, "LORD, in trouble they have visited you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They poured out a prayer when your chastening was on them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 26:17"}, "Just as a woman with child, who draws near the time of her delivery,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["is in pain and cries out in her pangs, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so we have been before you, LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 26:18"}, "We have been with child. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["We have been in pain. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["We gave birth, it seems, only to wind. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["We have not worked any deliverance in the earth; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["neither have the inhabitants of the world fallen. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 26:19"}, "Your dead shall live. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["My dead bodies shall arise. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Awake and sing, you who dwell in the dust; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for your dew is like the dew of herbs, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the earth will cast out the departed spirits. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 26:20"}, "Come, my people, enter into your rooms, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and shut your doors behind you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Hide yourself for a little moment, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["until the indignation is past. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 26:21"}, "For, behold, the LORD comes out of his place to punish the inhabitants of the earth for their iniquity.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The earth also will disclose her blood, and will no longer cover her slain.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "27", "sid": "ISA 27"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 27:1"}, "In that day, the LORD with his hard and great and strong sword will punish leviathan, the fleeing serpent, and leviathan\nthe twisted serpent; and he will kill the dragon that is in the sea.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 27:2"}, "In that day, sing to her, \u201cA pleasant vineyard! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 27:3"}, "I, the LORD, am its keeper. I will water it every moment. Lest anyone damage it, I will keep it night and day.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 27:4"}, "Wrath is not in me, but if I should find briers and thorns, I would do battle! I would march on them and I would burn them\ntogether. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 27:5"}, "Or else let him take hold of my strength, that he may make peace with me. Let him make peace with me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 27:6"}, "In days to come, Yaqub will take root. Israel will blossom and bud. They will fill the surface of the world with fruit.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 27:7"}, "Has he struck them as he struck those who struck them? Or are they killed like those who killed them were killed?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 27:8"}, "In measure, when you send them away, you contend with them. He has removed them with his rough blast in the day of the\neast wind. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 27:9"}, "Therefore by this the iniquity of Yaqub will be forgiven, and this is all the fruit of taking away his sin: that he makes\nall the stones of the altar as chalk stones that are beaten in pieces, so that the Asherah poles and the incense altars shall\nrise no more. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 27:10"}, "For the fortified city is solitary, a habitation deserted and forsaken, like the wilderness. The calf will feed there,\nand there he will lie down, and consume its branches. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 27:11"}, "When its boughs are withered, they will be broken off. The women will come and set them on fire, for they are a people of\nno understanding. Therefore he who made them will not have compassion on them, and he who formed them will show them no favour.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 27:12"}, "It will happen in that day that the LORD will thresh from the flowing stream of the Euphrates to the brook of Egypt; and\nyou will be gathered one by one, children of Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 27:13"}, "It will happen in that day that a great trumpet will be blown; and those who were ready to perish in the land of Assyria,\nand those who were outcasts in the land of Egypt, shall come; and they will worship the LORD in the holy mountain at Jerusalem.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "28", "sid": "ISA 28"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 28:1"}, "Woe to the crown of pride of the drunkards of Ephraim, and to the fading flower of his glorious beauty, which is on the\nhead of the fertile valley of those who are overcome with wine! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 28:2"}, "Behold, the Lord has a mighty and strong one. Like a storm of hail, a destroying storm, and like a storm of mighty waters\noverflowing, he will cast them down to the earth with his hand. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 28:3"}, "The crown of pride of the drunkards of Ephraim will be trodden under foot.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 28:4"}, "The fading flower of his glorious beauty, which is on the head of the fertile valley, shall be like the first-ripe fig\nbefore the summer; which someone picks and eats as soon as he sees it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 28:5"}, "In that day, the LORD of Armies will become a crown of glory and a diadem of beauty to the residue of his people,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 28:6"}, "and a spirit of justice to him who sits in judgement, and strength to those who turn back the battle at the gate.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 28:7"}, "They also reel with wine, and stagger with strong drink. The priest and the prophet reel with strong drink. They are\nswallowed up by wine. They stagger with strong drink. They err in vision. They stumble in judgement.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 28:8"}, "For all tables are completely full of filthy vomit and filthiness.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 28:9"}, "Whom will he teach knowledge? To whom will he explain the message? Those who are weaned from the milk, and drawn from the\nbreasts? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 28:10"}, "For it is precept on precept, precept on precept; line on line, line on line; here a little, there a little.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 28:11"}, "But he will speak to this nation with stammering lips and in another language,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 28:12"}, "to whom he said, \u201cThis is the resting place. Give rest to weary,\u201d and \u201cThis is the refreshing;\u201d yet they would not hear.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 28:13"}, "Therefore the LORD\u2019s word will be to them precept on precept, precept on precept; line on line, line on line; here a\nlittle, there a little; that they may go, fall backward, be broken, be snared, and be taken.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 28:14"}, "Therefore hear the LORD\u2019s word, you scoffers, that rule this people in Jerusalem:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 28:15"}, "\u201cBecause you have said, \u2018We have made a covenant with death, and we are in agreement with Sheol.\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["28:15 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Sheol is the place of the dead."]}], "caller": "+"}, " When the overflowing scourge passes through, it won\u2019t come to us; for we\nhave made lies our refuge, and we have hidden ourselves under falsehood.\u2019\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 28:16"}, "Therefore the Lord ALLAH says, \u201cBehold, I lay in Zion for a foundation a stone, a tried stone, a precious cornerstone of\na sure foundation. He who believes shall not act hastily. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 28:17"}, "I will make justice the measuring line, and righteousness the plumb line. The hail will sweep away the refuge of lies,\nand the waters will overflow the hiding place. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 28:18"}, "Your covenant with death shall be annulled, and your agreement with Sheol\n", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["28:18 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Sheol is the place of the dead."]}], "caller": "+"}, " shall not stand. When the overflowing scourge passes through, then you\nwill be trampled down by it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 28:19"}, "As often as it passes through, it will seize you; for morning by morning it will pass through, by day and by night; and\nit will be nothing but terror to understand the message.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 28:20"}, "For the bed is too short to stretch out on, and the blanket is too narrow to wrap oneself in.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 28:21"}, "For the LORD will rise up as on Mount Perazim. He will be angry as in the valley of Gibeon; that he may do his work, his\nunusual work, and bring to pass his act, his extraordinary act. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 28:22"}, "Now therefore don\u2019t be scoffers, lest your bonds be made strong; for I have heard a decree of destruction from the Lord,\nthe LORD of Armies, on the whole earth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 28:23"}, "Give ear, and hear my voice! Listen, and hear my speech! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 28:24"}, "Does he who ploughs to sow plough continually? Does he keep turning the soil and breaking the clods?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ISA 28:25"}, "When he has levelled its surface, doesn\u2019t he plant the dill, and scatter the cumin seed, and put in the wheat in rows,\nthe barley in the appointed place, and the spelt in its place? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ISA 28:26"}, "For his Allah instructs him in right judgement and teaches him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ISA 28:27"}, "For the dill are not threshed with a sharp instrument, neither is a cart wheel turned over the cumin; but the dill is\nbeaten out with a stick, and the cumin with a rod. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ISA 28:28"}, "Bread flour must be ground; so he will not always be threshing it. Although he drives the wheel of his threshing cart\nover it, his horses don\u2019t grind it. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ISA 28:29"}, "This also comes out from the LORD of Armies, who is wonderful in counsel, and excellent in wisdom.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "29", "sid": "ISA 29"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 29:1"}, "Woe to Ariel! Ariel, the city where Dawood encamped! Add year to year; let the feasts come around;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 29:2"}, "then I will distress Ariel, and there will be mourning and lamentation. She shall be to me as an altar\nhearth.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["29:2 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, Ariel"]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 29:3"}, "I will encamp against you all around you, and will lay siege against you with posted troops. I will raise siege works\nagainst you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 29:4"}, "You will be brought down, and will speak out of the ground. Your speech will mumble out of the dust. Your voice will be as\nof one who has a familiar spirit, out of the ground, and your speech will whisper out of the dust.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 29:5"}, "But the multitude of your foes will be like fine dust, and the multitude of the ruthless ones like chaff that blows away.\nYes, it will be in an instant, suddenly. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 29:6"}, "She will be visited by the LORD of Armies with thunder, with earthquake, with great noise, with whirlwind and storm, and\nwith the flame of a devouring fire. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 29:7"}, "The multitude of all the nations that fight against Ariel, even all who fight against her and her stronghold, and who\ndistress her, will be like a dream, a vision of the night. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 29:8"}, "It will be like when a hungry man dreams, and behold, he eats; but he awakes, and his hunger isn\u2019t satisfied; or like when\na thirsty man dreams, and behold, he drinks; but he awakes, and behold, he is faint, and he is still thirsty. The multitude of\nall the nations that fight against Mount Zion will be like that.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 29:9"}, "Pause and wonder! Blind yourselves and be blind! They are drunken, but not with wine; they stagger, but not with strong\ndrink. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 29:10"}, "For the LORD has poured out on you a spirit of deep sleep, and has closed your eyes, the prophets; and he has covered\nyour heads, the seers. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 29:11"}, "All vision has become to you like the words of a book that is sealed, which men deliver to one who is educated, saying,\n\u201cRead this, please;\u201d and he says, \u201cI can\u2019t, for it is sealed;\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 29:12"}, "and the book is delivered to one who is not educated, saying, \u201cRead this, please;\u201d and he says, \u201cI can\u2019t read.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 29:13"}, "The Lord said, \u201cBecause this people draws near with their mouth and honours me with their lips, but they have removed\ntheir heart far from me, and their fear of me is a commandment of men which has been taught;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 29:14"}, "therefore, behold, I will proceed to do a marvellous work amongst this people, even a marvellous work and a wonder; and\nthe wisdom of their wise men will perish, and the understanding of their prudent men will be hidden.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 29:15"}, "Woe to those who deeply hide their counsel from the LORD, and whose deeds are in the dark, and who say, \u201cWho sees us?\u201d\nand \u201cWho knows us?\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 29:16"}, "You turn things upside down! Should the potter be thought to be like clay; that the thing made should say about him who\nmade it, \u201cHe didn\u2019t make me;\u201d or the thing formed say of him who formed it, \u201cHe has no understanding?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 29:17"}, "Isn\u2019t it yet a very little while, and Lebanon will be turned into a fruitful field, and the fruitful field will be\nregarded as a forest? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 29:18"}, "In that day, the deaf will hear the words of the book, and the eyes of the blind will see out of obscurity and out of\ndarkness. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 29:19"}, "The humble also will increase their joy in the LORD, and the poor amongst men will rejoice in the Holy One of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 29:20"}, "For the ruthless is brought to nothing, and the scoffer ceases, and all those who are alert to do evil are cut off\u2014\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 29:21"}, "who cause a person to be indicted by a word, and lay a snare for the arbiter in the gate, and who deprive the innocent of\njustice with false testimony. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 29:22"}, "Therefore the LORD, who redeemed Ibrahim, says concerning the house of Yaqub: \u201cYaqub shall no longer be ashamed, neither\nshall his face grow pale. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 29:23"}, "But when he sees his children, the work of my hands, in the middle of him, they will sanctify my name. Yes, they will\nsanctify the Holy One of Yaqub, and will stand in awe of Allah of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 29:24"}, "They also who err in spirit will come to understanding, and those who grumble will receive instruction.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "30", "sid": "ISA 30"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 30:1"}, "\u201cWoe to the rebellious children\u201d, says the LORD, \u201cwho take counsel, but not from me; and who make an alliance, but not\nwith my Spirit, that they may add sin to sin, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 30:2"}, "who set out to go down into Egypt, and have not asked my advice, to strengthen themselves in the strength of Pharaoh, and\nto take refuge in the shadow of Egypt! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 30:3"}, "Therefore the strength of Pharaoh will be your shame, and the refuge in the shadow of Egypt your confusion.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 30:4"}, "For their princes are at Zoan, and their ambassadors have come to Hanes.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 30:5"}, "They shall all be ashamed because of a people that can\u2019t profit them, that are not a help nor profit, but a shame, and\nalso a reproach.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 30:6"}, "The burden of the animals of the South. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Through the land of trouble and anguish, of the lioness and the lion, the viper and fiery flying serpent, they carry their\nriches on the shoulders of young donkeys, and their treasures on the humps of camels, to an unprofitable people.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 30:7"}, "For Egypt helps in vain, and to no purpose; therefore I have called her Rahab who sits still.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 30:8"}, "Now go, write it before them on a tablet, and inscribe it in a book, that it may be for the time to come forever and ever.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 30:9"}, "For it is a rebellious people, lying children, children who will not hear the LORD\u2019s law;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 30:10"}, "who tell the seers, \u201cDon\u2019t see!\u201d and the prophets, \u201cDon\u2019t prophesy to us right things. Tell us pleasant things. Prophesy\ndeceits. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 30:11"}, "Get out of the way. Turn away from the path. Cause the Holy One of Israel to cease from before us.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 30:12"}, "Therefore the Holy One of Israel says, \u201cBecause you despise this word, and trust in oppression and perverseness, and rely\non it, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 30:13"}, "therefore this iniquity shall be to you like a breach ready to fall, swelling out in a high wall, whose breaking comes\nsuddenly in an instant. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 30:14"}, "He will break it as a potter\u2019s vessel is broken, breaking it in pieces without sparing, so that there won\u2019t be found\namongst the broken pieces a piece good enough to take fire from the hearth, or to dip up water out of the cistern.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 30:15"}, "For thus said the Lord ALLAH, the Holy One of Israel, \u201cYou will be saved in returning and rest. Your strength will be in\nquietness and in confidence.\u201d You refused, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 30:16"}, "but you said, \u201cNo, for we will flee on horses;\u201d therefore you will flee; and, \u201cWe will ride on the swift;\u201d therefore\nthose who pursue you will be swift. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 30:17"}, "One thousand will flee at the threat of one. At the threat of five, you will flee until you are left like a beacon on the\ntop of a mountain, and like a banner on a hill. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 30:18"}, "Therefore the LORD will wait, that he may be gracious to you; and therefore he will be exalted, that he may have mercy on\nyou, for the LORD is Allah of justice. Blessed are all those who wait for him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 30:19"}, "For the people will dwell in Zion at Jerusalem. You will weep no more. He will surely be gracious to you at the voice of\nyour cry. When he hears you, he will answer you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 30:20"}, "Though the Lord may give you the bread of adversity and the water of affliction, yet your teachers won\u2019t be hidden any\nmore, but your eyes will see your teachers; \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 30:21"}, "and when you turn to the right hand, and when you turn to the left, your ears will hear a voice behind you, saying, \u201cThis\nis the way. Walk in it.\u201d \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 30:22"}, "You shall defile the overlaying of your engraved images of silver, and the plating of your molten images of gold. You\nshall cast them away as an unclean thing. You shall tell it, \u201cGo away!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 30:23"}, "He will give the rain for your seed, with which you will sow the ground; and bread of the increase of the ground will be\nrich and plentiful. In that day, your livestock will feed in large pastures.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 30:24"}, "The oxen likewise and the young donkeys that till the ground will eat savoury feed, which has been winnowed with the\nshovel and with the fork. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ISA 30:25"}, "There will be brooks and streams of water on every lofty mountain and on every high hill in the day of the great\nslaughter, when the towers fall. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ISA 30:26"}, "Moreover the light of the moon will be like the light of the sun, and the light of the sun will be seven times brighter,\nlike the light of seven days, in the day that the LORD binds up the fracture of his people, and heals the wound they were\nstruck with. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ISA 30:27"}, "Behold, the LORD\u2019s name comes from far away, burning with his anger, and in thick rising smoke. His lips are full of\nindignation. His tongue is as a devouring fire. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ISA 30:28"}, "His breath is as an overflowing stream that reaches even to the neck, to sift the nations with the sieve of destruction.\nA bridle that leads to ruin will be in the jaws of the peoples. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ISA 30:29"}, "You will have a song, as in the night when a holy feast is kept, and gladness of heart, as when one goes with a flute to\ncome to the LORD\u2019s mountain, to Israel\u2019s Rock. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ISA 30:30"}, "The LORD will cause his glorious voice to be heard, and will show the descent of his arm, with the indignation of his\nanger, and the flame of a devouring fire, with a blast, storm, and hailstones.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ISA 30:31"}, "For through the LORD\u2019s voice the Assyrian will be dismayed. He will strike him with his rod.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ISA 30:32"}, "Every stroke of the rod of punishment, which the LORD will lay on him, will be with the sound of tambourines and harps.\nHe will fight with them in battles, brandishing weapons. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "ISA 30:33"}, "For his burning place has long been ready. Yes, for the king it is prepared. He has made its pyre deep and large with\nfire and much wood. The LORD\u2019s breath, like a stream of sulphur, kindles it.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "31", "sid": "ISA 31"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 31:1"}, "Woe to those who go down to Egypt for help, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and rely on horses, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and trust in chariots because they are many, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and in horsemen because they are very strong, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but they don\u2019t look to the Holy One of Israel, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and they don\u2019t seek the LORD! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 31:2"}, "Yet he also is wise, and will bring disaster, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will not call back his words, but will arise against the house of the evildoers,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and against the help of those who work iniquity. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 31:3"}, "Now the Egyptians are men, and not Allah; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and their horses flesh, and not spirit. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["When the LORD stretches out his hand, both he who helps shall stumble,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he who is helped shall fall, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and they all shall be consumed together. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 31:4"}, "For the LORD says to me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cAs the lion and the young lion growling over his prey, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["if a multitude of shepherds is called together against him, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["will not be dismayed at their voice, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor abase himself for their noise, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so the LORD of Armies will come down to fight on Mount Zion and on its heights.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 31:5"}, "As birds hovering, so the LORD of Armies will protect Jerusalem.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will protect and deliver it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will pass over and preserve it.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 31:6"}, "Return to him from whom you have deeply revolted, children of Israel.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 31:7"}, "For in that day everyone shall cast away his idols of silver and his idols of gold\u2014sin which your own hands have made for\nyou. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 31:8"}, "\u201cThe Assyrian will fall by the sword, not of man; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the sword, not of mankind, shall devour him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He will flee from the sword, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his young men will become subject to forced labour. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 31:9"}, "His rock will pass away by reason of terror, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his princes will be afraid of the banner,\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["says the LORD, whose fire is in Zion, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his furnace in Jerusalem. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "32", "sid": "ISA 32"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 32:1"}, "Behold, a king shall reign in righteousness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and princes shall rule in justice. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 32:2"}, "A man shall be as a hiding place from the wind, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a covert from the storm, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["as streams of water in a dry place, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["as the shade of a large rock in a weary land. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 32:3"}, "The eyes of those who see will not be dim, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the ears of those who hear will listen. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 32:4"}, "The heart of the rash will understand knowledge, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the tongue of the stammerers will be ready to speak plainly.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 32:5"}, "The fool will no longer be called noble, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor the scoundrel be highly respected. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 32:6"}, "For the fool will speak folly, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his heart will work iniquity, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to practise profanity, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and to utter error against the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to make empty the soul of the hungry, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and to cause the drink of the thirsty to fail. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 32:7"}, "The ways of the scoundrel are evil. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He devises wicked plans to destroy the humble with lying words,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["even when the needy speaks right. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 32:8"}, "But the noble devises noble things; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he will continue in noble things. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 32:9"}, "Rise up, you women who are at ease! Hear my voice! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You careless daughters, give ear to my speech! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 32:10"}, "For days beyond a year you will be troubled, you careless women;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for the vintage will fail. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The harvest won\u2019t come. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 32:11"}, "Tremble, you women who are at ease! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Be troubled, you careless ones! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Strip yourselves, make yourselves naked, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and put sackcloth on your waist. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 32:12"}, "Beat your breasts for the pleasant fields, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for the fruitful vine. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 32:13"}, "Thorns and briers will come up on my people\u2019s land; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["yes, on all the houses of joy in the joyous city. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 32:14"}, "For the palace will be forsaken. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The populous city will be deserted. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The hill and the watchtower will be for dens forever, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a delight for wild donkeys, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a pasture of flocks, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 32:15"}, "until the Spirit is poured on us from on high, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the wilderness becomes a fruitful field, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the fruitful field is considered a forest. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 32:16"}, "Then justice will dwell in the wilderness; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and righteousness will remain in the fruitful field. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 32:17"}, "The work of righteousness will be peace, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the effect of righteousness, quietness and confidence forever.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 32:18"}, "My people will live in a peaceful habitation, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["in safe dwellings, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and in quiet resting places, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 32:19"}, "though hail flattens the forest, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the city is levelled completely. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 32:20"}, "Blessed are you who sow beside all waters, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who send out the feet of the ox and the donkey. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "33", "sid": "ISA 33"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 33:1"}, "Woe to you who destroy, but you weren\u2019t destroyed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and who betray, but nobody betrayed you! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["When you have finished destroying, you will be destroyed; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and when you have finished betrayal, you will be betrayed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 33:2"}, "LORD, be gracious to us. We have waited for you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Be our strength every morning, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["our salvation also in the time of trouble. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 33:3"}, "At the noise of the thunder, the peoples have fled. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["When you lift yourself up, the nations are scattered. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 33:4"}, "Your plunder will be gathered as the caterpillar gathers. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Men will leap on it as locusts leap. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 33:5"}, "The LORD is exalted, for he dwells on high. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He has filled Zion with justice and righteousness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 33:6"}, "There will be stability in your times, abundance of salvation, wisdom, and knowledge.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The fear of the LORD is your treasure. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 33:7"}, "Behold, their valiant ones cry outside; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the ambassadors of peace weep bitterly. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 33:8"}, "The highways are desolate. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The travelling man ceases. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The covenant is broken. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He has despised the cities. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He doesn\u2019t respect man. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 33:9"}, "The land mourns and languishes. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Lebanon is confounded and withers away. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Sharon is like a desert, and Bashan and Carmel are stripped bare.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 33:10"}, "\u201cNow I will arise,\u201d says the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cNow I will lift myself up. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Now I will be exalted. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 33:11"}, "You will conceive chaff. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You will give birth to stubble. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Your breath is a fire that will devour you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 33:12"}, "The peoples will be like the burning of lime, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["like thorns that are cut down and burnt in the fire. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 33:13"}, "Hear, you who are far off, what I have done; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and, you who are near, acknowledge my might.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 33:14"}, "The sinners in Zion are afraid. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Trembling has seized the godless ones. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Who amongst us can live with the devouring fire? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Who amongst us can live with everlasting burning? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 33:15"}, "He who walks righteously \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and speaks blamelessly, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["he who despises the gain of oppressions, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who gestures with his hands, refusing to take a bribe, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who stops his ears from hearing of blood, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and shuts his eyes from looking at evil\u2014 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 33:16"}, "he will dwell on high. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["His place of defence will be the fortress of rocks. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["His bread will be supplied. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["His waters will be sure. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 33:17"}, "Your eyes will see the king in his beauty. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They will see a distant land. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 33:18"}, "Your heart will meditate on the terror. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Where is he who counted? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Where is he who weighed? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Where is he who counted the towers? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 33:19"}, "You will no longer see the fierce people, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a people of a deep speech that you can\u2019t comprehend, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["with a strange language that you can\u2019t understand. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 33:20"}, "Look at Zion, the city of our appointed festivals. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Your eyes will see Jerusalem, a quiet habitation, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a tent that won\u2019t be removed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Its stakes will never be plucked up, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor will any of its cords be broken. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 33:21"}, "But there the LORD will be with us in majesty, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a place of wide rivers and streams, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["in which no galley with oars will go, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["neither will any gallant ship pass by there. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 33:22"}, "For the LORD is our judge. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The LORD is our lawgiver. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The LORD is our king. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will save us. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 33:23"}, "Your rigging is untied. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They couldn\u2019t strengthen the foot of their mast. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They couldn\u2019t spread the sail. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Then the prey of a great plunder was divided. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The lame took the prey. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 33:24"}, "The inhabitant won\u2019t say, \u201cI am sick.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The people who dwell therein will be forgiven their iniquity.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "34", "sid": "ISA 34"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 34:1"}, "Come near, you nations, to hear! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Listen, you peoples. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let the earth and all it contains hear, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the world, and everything that comes from it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 34:2"}, "For the LORD is enraged against all the nations, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and angry with all their armies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He has utterly destroyed them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He has given them over for slaughter. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 34:3"}, "Their slain will also be cast out, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the stench of their dead bodies will come up. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The mountains will melt in their blood. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 34:4"}, "All of the army of the sky will be dissolved. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The sky will be rolled up like a scroll, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and all its armies will fade away, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["as a leaf fades from off a vine or a fig tree. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 34:5"}, "For my sword has drunk its fill in the sky. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Behold, it will come down on Edom, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and on the people of my curse, for judgement. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 34:6"}, "The LORD\u2019s sword is filled with blood. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["It is covered with fat, with the blood of lambs and goats, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["with the fat of the kidneys of rams; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for the LORD has a sacrifice in Bozrah, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["And a great slaughter in the land of Edom. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 34:7"}, "The wild oxen will come down with them, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the young bulls with the mighty bulls; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and their land will be drunken with blood, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and their dust made greasy with fat. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 34:8"}, "For the LORD has a day of vengeance, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a year of recompense for the cause of Zion. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 34:9"}, "Its streams will be turned into pitch, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["its dust into sulphur, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["And its land will become burning pitch. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 34:10"}, "It won\u2019t be quenched night nor day. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Its smoke will go up forever. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["From generation to generation, it will lie waste. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["No one will pass through it forever and ever. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 34:11"}, "But the pelican and the porcupine will possess it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The owl and the raven will dwell in it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He will stretch the line of confusion over it, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the plumb line of emptiness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 34:12"}, "They shall call its nobles to the kingdom, but none shall be there;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and all its princes shall be nothing. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 34:13"}, "Thorns will come up in its palaces, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nettles and thistles in its fortresses; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and it will be a habitation of jackals, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a court for ostriches. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 34:14"}, "The wild animals of the desert will meet with the wolves, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the wild goat will cry to his fellow. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Yes, the night creature", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["34:14 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["literally, lilith, which could also be a night demon or night\nmonster"]}], "caller": "+"}, " shall settle there, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and shall find herself a place of rest. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 34:15"}, "The arrow snake will make her nest there, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and lay, hatch, and gather under her shade. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, the kites will be gathered there, every one with her mate.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 34:16"}, "Search in the book of the LORD, and read: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["not one of these will be missing. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["None will lack her mate. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["For my mouth has commanded, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his Spirit has gathered them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 34:17"}, "He has cast the lot for them, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his hand has divided it to them with a measuring line. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They shall possess it forever. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["From generation to generation they will dwell in it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "35", "sid": "ISA 35"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 35:1"}, "The wilderness and the dry land will be glad. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The desert will rejoice and blossom like a rose. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 35:2"}, "It will blossom abundantly, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and rejoice even with joy and singing. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Lebanon\u2019s glory will be given to it, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the excellence of Carmel and Sharon. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They will see the LORD\u2019s glory, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the excellence of our Allah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 35:3"}, "Strengthen the weak hands, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and make the feeble knees firm. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 35:4"}, "Tell those who have a fearful heart, \u201cBe strong! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Don\u2019t be afraid! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Behold, your Allah will come with vengeance, Allah\u2019s retribution.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will come and save you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 35:5"}, "Then the eyes of the blind will be opened, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the ears of the deaf will be unstopped. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 35:6"}, "Then the lame man will leap like a deer, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the tongue of the mute will sing; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for waters will break out in the wilderness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and streams in the desert. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 35:7"}, "The burning sand will become a pool, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the thirsty ground springs of water. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Grass with reeds and rushes will be in the habitation of jackals, where they lay.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 35:8"}, "A highway will be there, a road, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and it will be called \u201cThe Holy Way\u201d. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["The unclean shall not pass over it, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but it will be for those who walk in the Way. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Wicked fools shall not go there. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 35:9"}, "No lion will be there, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor will any ravenous animal go up on it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They will not be found there; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but the redeemed will walk there. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 35:10"}, "Then the LORD\u2019s ransomed ones will return, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and come with singing to Zion; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and everlasting joy will be on their heads. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They will obtain gladness and joy, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and sorrow and sighing will flee away.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "36", "sid": "ISA 36"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 36:1"}, "Now in the fourteenth year of king Hezekiah, Sennacherib king of Assyria attacked all of the fortified cities of Judah and\ncaptured them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 36:2"}, "The king of Assyria sent Rabshakeh from Lachish to Jerusalem to king Hezekiah with a large army. He stood by the aqueduct\nfrom the upper pool in the fuller\u2019s field highway. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 36:3"}, "Then Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, who was over the household, and Shebna the scribe, and Joah, the son of Asaph, the\nrecorder came out to him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 36:4"}, "Rabshakeh said to them, \u201cNow tell Hezekiah, \u2018The great king, the king of Assyria, says, \u201cWhat confidence is this in which\nyou trust? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 36:5"}, "I say that your counsel and strength for the war are only vain words. Now in whom do you trust, that you have rebelled\nagainst me? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 36:6"}, "Behold, you trust in the staff of this bruised reed, even in Egypt, which if a man leans on it, it will go into his hand\nand pierce it. So is Pharaoh king of Egypt to all who trust in him.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 36:7"}, "But if you tell me, \u2018We trust in the LORD our Allah,\u2019 isn\u2019t that he whose high places and whose altars Hezekiah has taken\naway, and has said to Judah and to Jerusalem, \u2018You shall worship before this altar?\u2019\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 36:8"}, "Now therefore, please make a pledge to my master the king of Assyria, and I will give you two thousand horses, if you are\nable on your part to set riders on them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 36:9"}, "How then can you turn away the face of one captain of the least of my master\u2019s servants, and put your trust on Egypt for\nchariots and for horsemen? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 36:10"}, "Have I come up now without the LORD against this land to destroy it? the LORD said to me, \u201cGo up against this land, and\ndestroy it.\u201d\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 36:11"}, "Then Eliakim, Shebna and Joah said to Rabshakeh, \u201cPlease speak to your servants in Aramaic, for we understand it. Don\u2019t\nspeak to us in the Jews\u2019 language in the hearing of the people who are on the wall.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 36:12"}, "But Rabshakeh said, \u201cHas my master sent me only to your master and to you, to speak these words, and not to the men who\nsit on the wall, who will eat their own dung and drink their own urine with you?\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 36:13"}, "Then Rabshakeh stood, and called out with a loud voice in the Jews\u2019 language, and said, \u201cHear the words of the great\nking, the king of Assyria! \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 36:14"}, "The king says, \u2018Don\u2019t let Hezekiah deceive you; for he will not be able to deliver you.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 36:15"}, "Don\u2019t let Hezekiah make you trust in the LORD, saying, \u201cThe LORD will surely deliver us. This city won\u2019t be given into\nthe hand of the king of Assyria.\u201d\u2019 \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 36:16"}, "Don\u2019t listen to Hezekiah, for the king of Assyria says, \u2018Make your peace with me, and come out to me; and each of you eat\nfrom his vine, and each one from his fig tree, and each one of you drink the waters of his own cistern;\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 36:17"}, "until I come and take you away to a land like your own land, a land of grain and new wine, a land of bread and vineyards.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 36:18"}, "Beware lest Hezekiah persuade you, saying, \u201cThe LORD will deliver us.\u201d Have any of the gods of the nations delivered\ntheir lands from the hand of the king of Assyria? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 36:19"}, "Where are the gods of Hamath and Arpad? Where are the gods of Sepharvaim? Have they delivered Samaria from my hand?\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 36:20"}, "Who are they amongst all the gods of these countries that have delivered their country out of my hand, that the LORD\nshould deliver Jerusalem out of my hand?\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 36:21"}, "But they remained silent, and said nothing in reply, for the king\u2019s commandment was, \u201cDon\u2019t answer him.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 36:22"}, "Then Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, who was over the household, and Shebna the scribe, and Joah, the son of Asaph, the\nrecorder, came to Hezekiah with their clothes torn, and told him the words of Rabshakeh.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "37", "sid": "ISA 37"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 37:1"}, "When king Hezekiah heard it, he tore his clothes, covered himself with sackcloth, and went into the LORD\u2019s house.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 37:2"}, "He sent Eliakim, who was over the household, and Shebna the scribe, and the elders of the priests, covered with sackcloth,\nto Isaiah the prophet, the son of Amoz. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 37:3"}, "They said to him, \u201cHezekiah says, \u2018Today is a day of trouble, and of rebuke, and of rejection; for the children have come\nto the birth, and there is no strength to give birth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 37:4"}, "It may be Allah your LORD will hear the words of Rabshakeh, whom the king of Assyria his master has sent to defy the\nliving Allah, and will rebuke the words which Allah your LORD has heard. Therefore lift up your prayer for the remnant that is\nleft.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 37:5"}, "So the servants of king Hezekiah came to Isaiah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 37:6"}, "Isaiah said to them, \u201cTell your master, \u2018The LORD says, \u201cDon\u2019t be afraid of the words that you have heard, with which the\nservants of the king of Assyria have blasphemed me. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 37:7"}, "Behold, I will put a spirit in him and he will hear news, and will return to his own land. I will cause him to fall by the\nsword in his own land.\u201d\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 37:8"}, "So Rabshakeh returned, and found the king of Assyria warring against Libnah, for he had heard that he was departed from\nLachish. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 37:9"}, "He heard news concerning Tirhakah king of Ethiopia, \u201cHe has come out to fight against you.\u201d When he heard it, he sent\nmessengers to Hezekiah, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 37:10"}, "\u201cThus you shall speak to Hezekiah king of Judah, saying, \u2018Don\u2019t let your Allah in whom you trust deceive you, saying,\n\u201cJerusalem won\u2019t be given into the hand of the king of Assyria.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 37:11"}, "Behold, you have heard what the kings of Assyria have done to all lands, by destroying them utterly. Shall you be\ndelivered? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 37:12"}, "Have the gods of the nations delivered them, which my fathers have destroyed, Gozan, Haran, Rezeph, and the children of\nEden who were in Telassar? \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 37:13"}, "Where is the king of Hamath, and the king of Arpad, and the king of the city of Sepharvaim, of Hena, and Ivvah?\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 37:14"}, "Hezekiah received the letter from the hand of the messengers and read it. Then Hezekiah went up to the LORD\u2019s house, and\nspread it before the LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 37:15"}, "Hezekiah prayed to the LORD, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 37:16"}, "\u201cLORD of Armies, Allah of Israel, who is enthroned amongst the cherubim, you are Allah, even you alone, of all the\nkingdoms of the earth. You have made heaven and earth. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 37:17"}, "Turn your ear, LORD, and hear. Open your eyes, LORD, and behold. Hear all of the words of Sennacherib, who has sent to\ndefy the living Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 37:18"}, "Truly, LORD, the kings of Assyria have destroyed all the countries and their land,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 37:19"}, "and have cast their gods into the fire; for they were no gods, but the work of men\u2019s hands, wood and stone; therefore\nthey have destroyed them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 37:20"}, "Now therefore, LORD our Allah, save us from his hand, that all the kingdoms of the earth may know that you are the LORD,\neven you only.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 37:21"}, "Then Isaiah the son of Amoz sent to Hezekiah, saying, \u201cThe LORD, Allah of Israel says, \u2018Because you have prayed to me\nagainst Sennacherib king of Assyria, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 37:22"}, "this is the word which the LORD has spoken concerning him. The virgin daughter of Zion has despised you and ridiculed\nyou. The daughter of Jerusalem has shaken her head at you. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 37:23"}, "Whom have you defied and blasphemed? Against whom have you exalted your voice and lifted up your eyes on high? Against\nthe Holy One of Israel. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 37:24"}, "By your servants, you have defied the Lord, and have said, \u201cWith the multitude of my chariots I have come up to the\nheight of the mountains, to the innermost parts of Lebanon. I will cut down its tall cedars and its choice cypress trees. I\nwill enter into its farthest height, the forest of its fruitful field.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ISA 37:25"}, "I have dug and drunk water, and with the sole of my feet I will dry up all the rivers of Egypt.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ISA 37:26"}, "\u201c\u2018Have you not heard how I have done it long ago, and formed it in ancient times? Now I have brought it to pass, that it\nshould be yours to destroy fortified cities, turning them into ruinous heaps.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ISA 37:27"}, "Therefore their inhabitants had little power. They were dismayed and confounded. They were like the grass of the field,\nand like the green herb, like the grass on the housetops, and like a field before its crop has grown.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ISA 37:28"}, "But I know your sitting down, your going out, your coming in, and your raging against me.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ISA 37:29"}, "Because of your raging against me, and because your arrogance has come up into my ears, therefore I will put my hook in\nyour nose and my bridle in your lips, and I will turn you back by the way by which you came.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ISA 37:30"}, "\u201c\u2018This shall be the sign to you. You will eat this year that which grows of itself, and in the second year that which\nsprings from it; and in the third year sow and reap and plant vineyards, and eat their fruit.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ISA 37:31"}, "The remnant that is escaped of the house of Judah will again take root downward, and bear fruit upward.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "32", "sid": "ISA 37:32"}, "For out of Jerusalem a remnant will go out, and survivors will escape from Mount Zion. The zeal of the LORD of Armies\nwill perform this.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "33", "sid": "ISA 37:33"}, "\u201cTherefore the LORD says concerning the king of Assyria, \u2018He will not come to this city, nor shoot an arrow there,\nneither will he come before it with shield, nor cast up a mound against it.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "34", "sid": "ISA 37:34"}, "He will return the way that he came, and he won\u2019t come to this city,\u2019 says the LORD.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "35", "sid": "ISA 37:35"}, "\u2018For I will defend this city to save it, for my own sake, and for my servant Dawood\u2019s sake.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "36", "sid": "ISA 37:36"}, "Then the LORD\u2019s angel went out and struck one hundred and eighty-five thousand men in the camp of the Assyrians. When men\narose early in the morning, behold, these were all dead bodies. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "37", "sid": "ISA 37:37"}, "So Sennacherib king of Assyria departed, went away, returned to Nineveh, and stayed there.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "38", "sid": "ISA 37:38"}, "As he was worshipping in the house of Nisroch his god, Adrammelech and Sharezer his sons struck him with the sword; and\nthey escaped into the land of Ararat. Esar Haddon his son reigned in his place.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "38", "sid": "ISA 38"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 38:1"}, "In those days Hezekiah was sick and near death. Isaiah the prophet, the son of Amoz, came to him, and said to him, \u201cThe\nLORD says, \u2018Set your house in order, for you will die, and not live.\u2019\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 38:2"}, "Then Hezekiah turned his face to the wall and prayed to the LORD,\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 38:3"}, "and said, \u201cRemember now, the LORD, I beg you, how I have walked before you in truth and with a perfect heart, and have\ndone that which is good in your sight.\u201d Then Hezekiah wept bitterly.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 38:4"}, "Then the LORD\u2019s word came to Isaiah, saying, \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 38:5"}, "\u201cGo, and tell Hezekiah, \u2018The LORD, Allah of Dawood your father, says, \u201cI have heard your prayer. I have seen your tears.\nBehold, I will add fifteen years to your life. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 38:6"}, "I will deliver you and this city out of the hand of the king of Assyria, and I will defend this city.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 38:7"}, "This shall be the sign to you from the LORD, that the LORD will do this thing that he has spoken.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 38:8"}, "Behold, I will cause the shadow on the sundial, which has gone down on the sundial of Ahaz with the sun, to return\nbackward ten steps.\u201d\u2019\u201d So the sun returned ten steps on the sundial on which it had gone down.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 38:9"}, "The writing of Hezekiah king of Judah, when he had been sick, and had recovered of his sickness.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 38:10"}, "I said, \u201cIn the middle of my life I go into the gates of Sheol.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": [" \n", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["38:10 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Sheol is the place of the dead."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I am deprived of the residue of my years.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 38:11"}, "I said, \u201cI won\u2019t see the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The LORD in the land of the living. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will see man no more with the inhabitants of the world. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 38:12"}, "My dwelling is removed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and is carried away from me like a shepherd\u2019s tent. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I have rolled up my life like a weaver. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will cut me off from the loom. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["From day even to night you will make an end of me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 38:13"}, "I waited patiently until morning. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He breaks all my bones like a lion. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["From day even to night you will make an end of me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 38:14"}, "I chattered like a swallow or a crane. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I moaned like a dove. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["My eyes weaken looking upward. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Lord, I am oppressed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Be my security.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 38:15"}, "What will I say? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He has both spoken to me, and himself has done it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will walk carefully all my years because of the anguish of my soul.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 38:16"}, "Lord, men live by these things; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and my spirit finds life in all of them: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["you restore me, and cause me to live. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 38:17"}, "Behold, for peace I had great anguish, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but you have in love for my soul delivered it from the pit of corruption;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for you have cast all my sins behind your back. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 38:18"}, "For Sheol", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["38:18 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Sheol is the place of the dead."]}], "caller": "+"}, " can\u2019t praise you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Death can\u2019t celebrate you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Those who go down into the pit can\u2019t hope for your truth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 38:19"}, "The living, the living, he shall praise you, as I do today.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The father shall make known your truth to the children. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 38:20"}, "The LORD will save me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Therefore we will sing my songs with stringed instruments all the days of our life in the LORD\u2019s house.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 38:21"}, "Now Isaiah had said, \u201cLet them take a cake of figs, and lay it for a poultice on the boil, and he shall recover.\u201d\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 38:22"}, "Hezekiah also had said, \u201cWhat is the sign that I will go up to the LORD\u2019s house?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "39", "sid": "ISA 39"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 39:1"}, "At that time, Merodach Baladan the son of Baladan, king of Babylon, sent letters and a present to Hezekiah; for he heard\nthat he had been sick, and had recovered. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 39:2"}, "Hezekiah was pleased with them, and showed them the house of his precious things, the silver, the gold, the spices, and\nthe precious oil, and all the house of his armour, and all that was found in his treasures. There was nothing in his house, nor\nin all his dominion, that Hezekiah didn\u2019t show them. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 39:3"}, "Then Isaiah the prophet came to king Hezekiah, and asked him, \u201cWhat did these men say? From where did they come to you?\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Hezekiah said, \u201cThey have come from a country far from me, even from Babylon.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 39:4"}, "Then he asked, \u201cWhat have they seen in your house?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": ["Hezekiah answered, \u201cThey have seen all that is in my house. There is nothing amongst my treasures that I have not shown\nthem.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 39:5"}, "Then Isaiah said to Hezekiah, \u201cHear the word of the LORD of Armies:\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 39:6"}, "\u2018Behold, the days are coming when all that is in your house, and that which your fathers have stored up until today, will\nbe carried to Babylon. Nothing will be left,\u2019 says the LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 39:7"}, "\u2018They will take away your sons who will issue from you, whom you shall father, and they will be eunuchs in the king of\nBabylon\u2019s palace.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 39:8"}, "Then Hezekiah said to Isaiah, \u201cThe LORD\u2019s word which you have spoken is good.\u201d He said moreover, \u201cFor there will be peace\nand truth in my days.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "40", "sid": "ISA 40"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 40:1"}, "\u201cComfort, comfort my people,\u201d says your Allah. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 40:2"}, "\u201cSpeak comfortably to Jerusalem; and call out to her that her warfare is accomplished, that her iniquity is pardoned, that\nshe has received of the LORD\u2019s hand double for all her sins.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 40:3"}, "The voice of one who calls out, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cPrepare the way of the LORD in the wilderness! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Make a level highway in the desert for our Allah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 40:4"}, "Every valley shall be exalted, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and every mountain and hill shall be made low. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The uneven shall be made level, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the rough places a plain. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 40:5"}, "The LORD\u2019s glory shall be revealed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and all flesh shall see it together; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for the mouth of the LORD has spoken it.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 40:6"}, "The voice of one saying, \u201cCry!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["One said, \u201cWhat shall I cry?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cAll flesh is like grass, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and all its glory is like the flower of the field. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 40:7"}, "The grass withers, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the flower fades, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["because the LORD\u2019s breath blows on it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Surely the people are like grass. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 40:8"}, "The grass withers, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the flower fades; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but the word of our Allah stands forever.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 40:9"}, "You who tell good news to Zion, go up on a high mountain. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You who tell good news to Jerusalem, lift up your voice with strength!\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Lift it up! Don\u2019t be afraid! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Say to the cities of Judah, \u201cBehold, your Allah!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 40:10"}, "Behold, the Lord ALLAH will come as a mighty one, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his arm will rule for him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Behold, his reward is with him, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his recompense before him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 40:11"}, "He will feed his flock like a shepherd. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will gather the lambs in his arm, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and carry them in his bosom. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will gently lead those who have their young. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 40:12"}, "Who has measured the waters in the hollow of his hand, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and marked off the sky with his span, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and calculated the dust of the earth in a measuring basket, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and weighed the mountains in scales, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the hills in a balance? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 40:13"}, "Who has directed the LORD\u2019s Spirit, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["or has taught him as his counsellor? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 40:14"}, "Who did he take counsel with, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and who instructed him, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and taught him in the path of justice, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and taught him knowledge, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and showed him the way of understanding? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 40:15"}, "Behold, the nations are like a drop in a bucket, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and are regarded as a speck of dust on a balance. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Behold, he lifts up the islands like a very little thing. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 40:16"}, "Lebanon is not sufficient to burn, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor its animals sufficient for a burnt offering. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 40:17"}, "All the nations are like nothing before him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They are regarded by him as less than nothing, and vanity. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 40:18"}, "To whom then will you liken Allah? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Or what likeness will you compare to him? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 40:19"}, "A workman has cast an image, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the goldsmith overlays it with gold, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and casts silver chains for it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 40:20"}, "He who is too impoverished for such an offering chooses a tree that will not rot.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He seeks a skilful workman to set up a carved image for him that will not be moved.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 40:21"}, "Haven\u2019t you known? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Haven\u2019t you heard? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Haven\u2019t you been told from the beginning? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Haven\u2019t you understood from the foundations of the earth? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 40:22"}, "It is he who sits above the circle of the earth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and its inhabitants are like grasshoppers; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who stretches out the heavens like a curtain, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and spreads them out like a tent to dwell in, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 40:23"}, "who brings princes to nothing, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who makes the judges of the earth meaningless. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 40:24"}, "They are planted scarcely. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They are sown scarcely. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Their stock has scarcely taken root in the ground. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He merely blows on them, and they wither, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the whirlwind takes them away as stubble. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ISA 40:25"}, "\u201cTo whom then will you liken me? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Who is my equal?\u201d says the Holy One. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ISA 40:26"}, "Lift up your eyes on high, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and see who has created these, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who brings out their army by number. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He calls them all by name. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["by the greatness of his might, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and because he is strong in power, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["not one is lacking. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ISA 40:27"}, "Why do you say, Yaqub, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and speak, Israel, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cMy way is hidden from the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the justice due me is disregarded by my Allah?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ISA 40:28"}, "Haven\u2019t you known? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Haven\u2019t you heard? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The everlasting Allah, the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the Creator of the ends of the earth, doesn\u2019t faint. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He isn\u2019t weary. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["His understanding is unsearchable. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ISA 40:29"}, "He gives power to the weak. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He increases the strength of him who has no might. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "30", "sid": "ISA 40:30"}, "Even the youths faint and get weary, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the young men utterly fall; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "31", "sid": "ISA 40:31"}, "but those who wait for the LORD will renew their strength.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They will mount up with wings like eagles. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They will run, and not be weary. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They will walk, and not faint. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "41", "sid": "ISA 41"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 41:1"}, "\u201cKeep silent before me, islands, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and let the peoples renew their strength. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Let them come near, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["then let them speak. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let\u2019s meet together for judgement. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 41:2"}, "Who has raised up one from the east? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Who called him to his foot in righteousness? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He hands over nations to him \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and makes him rule over kings. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He gives them like the dust to his sword, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["like the driven stubble to his bow. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 41:3"}, "He pursues them \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and passes by safely, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["even by a way that he had not gone with his feet. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 41:4"}, "Who has worked and done it, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["calling the generations from the beginning? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I, the LORD, the first, and with the last, I am he.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 41:5"}, "The islands have seen, and fear. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The ends of the earth tremble. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They approach, and come. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 41:6"}, "Everyone helps his neighbour. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They say to their brothers, \u201cBe strong!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 41:7"}, "So the carpenter encourages the goldsmith. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He who smoothes with the hammer encourages him who strikes the anvil,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["saying of the soldering, \u201cIt is good;\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he fastens it with nails, that it might not totter. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 41:8"}, "\u201cBut you, Israel, my servant, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yaqub whom I have chosen, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the offspring of Ibrahim my friend, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 41:9"}, "You whom I have taken hold of from the ends of the earth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and called from its corners, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and said to you, \u2018You are my servant, I have chosen you and have not cast you away.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 41:10"}, "Don\u2019t you be afraid, for I am with you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Don\u2019t be dismayed, for I am your Allah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will strengthen you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, I will help you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, I will uphold you with the right hand of my righteousness.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 41:11"}, "Behold, all those who are incensed against you will be disappointed and confounded.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Those who strive with you will be like nothing, and shall perish.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 41:12"}, "You will seek them, and won\u2019t find them, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["even those who contend with you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Those who war against you will be as nothing, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["as a non-existent thing. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 41:13"}, "For I, Allah your LORD, will hold your right hand, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["saying to you, \u2018Don\u2019t be afraid. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will help you.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 41:14"}, "Don\u2019t be afraid, you worm Yaqub, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and you men of Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will help you,\u201d says the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cYour Redeemer is the Holy One of Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 41:15"}, "Behold, I have made you into a new sharp threshing instrument with teeth.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You will thresh the mountains, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and beat them small, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will make the hills like chaff. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 41:16"}, "You will winnow them, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the wind will carry them away, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the whirlwind will scatter them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["You will rejoice in the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You will glory in the Holy One of Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 41:17"}, "The poor and needy seek water, and there is none. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Their tongue fails for thirst. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I, the LORD, will answer them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I, Allah of Israel, will not forsake them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 41:18"}, "I will open rivers on the bare heights, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and springs in the middle of the valleys. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will make the wilderness a pool of water, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the dry land springs of water. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 41:19"}, "I will put cedar, acacia, myrtle, and oil trees in the wilderness.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will set cypress trees, pine, and box trees together in the desert;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 41:20"}, "that they may see, know, consider, and understand together,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that the LORD\u2019s hand has done this, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the Holy One of Israel has created it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 41:21"}, "Produce your cause,\u201d says the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cBring out your strong reasons!\u201d says the King of Yaqub. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 41:22"}, "\u201cLet them announce and declare to us what will happen! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Declare the former things, what they are, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that we may consider them, and know the latter end of them; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["or show us things to come. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 41:23"}, "Declare the things that are to come hereafter, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that we may know that you are gods. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Yes, do good, or do evil, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that we may be dismayed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and see it together. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 41:24"}, "Behold, you are nothing, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your work is nothing. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He who chooses you is an abomination. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ISA 41:25"}, "\u201cI have raised up one from the north, and he has come, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["from the rising of the sun, one who calls on my name, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he shall come on rulers as on mortar, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and as the potter treads clay. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ISA 41:26"}, "Who has declared it from the beginning, that we may know? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and before, that we may say, \u2018He is right?\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Surely, there is no one who declares. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Surely, there is no one who shows. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Surely, there is no one who hears your words. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ISA 41:27"}, "I am the first to say to Zion, \u2018Behold, look at them;\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I will give one who brings good news to Jerusalem. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ISA 41:28"}, "When I look, there is no man, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["even amongst them there is no counsellor who, when I ask of them, can answer a word.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "29", "sid": "ISA 41:29"}, "Behold, all of their deeds are vanity and nothing. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Their molten images are wind and confusion. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "42", "sid": "ISA 42"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 42:1"}, "\u201cBehold, my servant, whom I uphold, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["my chosen, in whom my soul delights: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I have put my Spirit on him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will bring justice to the nations. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 42:2"}, "He will not shout, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor raise his voice, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor cause it to be heard in the street. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 42:3"}, "He won\u2019t break a bruised reed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He won\u2019t quench a dimly burning wick. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will faithfully bring justice. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 42:4"}, "He will not fail nor be discouraged, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["until he has set justice in the earth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the islands wait for his law.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 42:5"}, "Allah the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["he who created the heavens and stretched them out, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["he who spread out the earth and that which comes out of it, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["he who gives breath to its people and spirit to those who walk in it, says:\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 42:6"}, "\u201cI, the LORD, have called you in righteousness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will hold your hand. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will keep you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and make you a covenant for the people, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["as a light for the nations, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 42:7"}, "to open the blind eyes, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to bring the prisoners out of the dungeon, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and those who sit in darkness out of the prison. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 42:8"}, "\u201cI am the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["That is my name. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will not give my glory to another, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor my praise to engraved images. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 42:9"}, "Behold, the former things have happened \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I declare new things. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I tell you about them before they come up.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 42:10"}, "Sing to the LORD a new song, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his praise from the end of the earth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["you who go down to the sea, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and all that is therein, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the islands and their inhabitants. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 42:11"}, "Let the wilderness and its cities raise their voices, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["with the villages that Kedar inhabits. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let the inhabitants of Sela sing. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let them shout from the top of the mountains! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 42:12"}, "Let them give glory to the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and declare his praise in the islands. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 42:13"}, "The LORD will go out like a mighty man. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will stir up zeal like a man of war. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will raise a war cry. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, he will shout aloud. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will triumph over his enemies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 42:14"}, "\u201cI have been silent a long time. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I have been quiet and restrained myself. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Now I will cry out like a travailing woman. I will both gasp and pant.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 42:15"}, "I will destroy mountains and hills, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and dry up all their herbs. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will make the rivers islands, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will dry up the pools. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 42:16"}, "I will bring the blind by a way that they don\u2019t know. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will lead them in paths that they don\u2019t know. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will make darkness light before them, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and crooked places straight. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will do these things, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I will not forsake them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 42:17"}, "\u201cThose who trust in engraved images, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who tell molten images, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u2018You are our gods,\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["will be turned back. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They will be utterly disappointed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 42:18"}, "\u201cHear, you deaf, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and look, you blind, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that you may see. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 42:19"}, "Who is blind, but my servant? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Or who is as deaf as my messenger whom I send? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Who is as blind as he who is at peace, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and as blind as the LORD\u2019s servant? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 42:20"}, "You see many things, but don\u2019t observe. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["His ears are open, but he doesn\u2019t listen. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 42:21"}, "It pleased the LORD, for his righteousness\u2019 sake, to magnify the law\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and make it honourable. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 42:22"}, "But this is a robbed and plundered people. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["All of them are snared in holes, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and they are hidden in prisons. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They have become captives, and no one delivers, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a plunder, and no one says, \u2018Restore them!\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 42:23"}, "Who is there amongst you who will give ear to this? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Who will listen and hear for the time to come? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 42:24"}, "Who gave Yaqub as plunder, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and Israel to the robbers? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Didn\u2019t the LORD, he against whom we have sinned? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["For they would not walk in his ways, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and they disobeyed his law. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ISA 42:25"}, "Therefore he poured the fierceness of his anger on him, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the strength of battle. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["It set him on fire all around, but he didn\u2019t know. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["It burnt him, but he didn\u2019t take it to heart.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "43", "sid": "ISA 43"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 43:1"}, "But now the LORD who created you, Yaqub, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he who formed you, Israel, says: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cDon\u2019t be afraid, for I have redeemed you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I have called you by your name. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You are mine. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 43:2"}, "When you pass through the waters, I will be with you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and through the rivers, they will not overflow you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["When you walk through the fire, you will not be burnt, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and flame will not scorch you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 43:3"}, "For I am Allah your LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the Holy One of Israel, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["your Saviour. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I have given Egypt as your ransom, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Ethiopia and Seba in your place. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 43:4"}, "Since you have been precious and honoured in my sight, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I have loved you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["therefore I will give people in your place, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and nations instead of your life. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 43:5"}, "Don\u2019t be afraid, for I am with you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will bring your offspring from the east, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and gather you from the west. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 43:6"}, "I will tell the north, \u2018Give them up!\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and tell the south, \u2018Don\u2019t hold them back! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Bring my sons from far away, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and my daughters from the ends of the earth\u2014 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 43:7"}, "everyone who is called by my name, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and whom I have created for my glory, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["whom I have formed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["yes, whom I have made.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 43:8"}, "Bring out the blind people who have eyes, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the deaf who have ears. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 43:9"}, "Let all the nations be gathered together, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and let the peoples be assembled. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Who amongst them can declare this, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and show us former things? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Let them bring their witnesses, that they may be justified, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["or let them hear, and say, \u201cThat is true.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 43:10"}, "\u201cYou are my witnesses,\u201d says the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cWith my servant whom I have chosen; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that you may know and believe me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and understand that I am he. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Before me there was no Allah formed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["neither will there be after me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 43:11"}, "I myself am the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Besides me, there is no saviour. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 43:12"}, "I have declared, I have saved, and I have shown, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and there was no strange god amongst you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Therefore you are my witnesses\u201d, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["says the LORD, \u201cand I am Allah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 43:13"}, "Yes, since the day was, I am he. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["There is no one who can deliver out of my hand. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will work, and who can hinder it?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 43:14"}, "The LORD, your Redeemer, the Holy One of Israel says: \u201cFor your sake, I have sent to Babylon, and I will bring all of\nthem down as fugitives, even the Chaldeans, in the ships of their rejoicing.\n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 43:15"}, "I am the LORD, your Holy One, the Creator of Israel, your King.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 43:16"}, "The LORD, who makes a way in the sea, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a path in the mighty waters, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 43:17"}, "who brings out the chariot and horse, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the army and the mighty man \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["(they lie down together, they shall not rise; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["they are extinct, they are quenched like a wick) says: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 43:18"}, "\u201cDon\u2019t remember the former things, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and don\u2019t consider the things of old. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 43:19"}, "Behold, I will do a new thing. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["It springs out now. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Don\u2019t you know it? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I will even make a way in the wilderness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and rivers in the desert. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 43:20"}, "The animals of the field, the jackals and the ostriches, shall honour me,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["because I give water in the wilderness and rivers in the desert,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to give drink to my people, my chosen, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 43:21"}, "the people which I formed for myself, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that they might declare my praise. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 43:22"}, "Yet you have not called on me, Yaqub; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but you have been weary of me, Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 43:23"}, "You have not brought me any of your sheep for burnt offerings,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["neither have you honoured me with your sacrifices. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I have not burdened you with offerings, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor wearied you with frankincense. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 43:24"}, "You have bought me no sweet cane with money, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor have you filled me with the fat of your sacrifices, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["but you have burdened me with your sins. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You have wearied me with your iniquities. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ISA 43:25"}, "I, even I, am he who blots out your transgressions for my own sake;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I will not remember your sins. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ISA 43:26"}, "Put me in remembrance. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let us plead together. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Declare your case, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that you may be justified. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ISA 43:27"}, "Your first father sinned, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your teachers have transgressed against me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ISA 43:28"}, "Therefore I will profane the princes of the sanctuary; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I will make Yaqub a curse, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and Israel an insult.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "44", "sid": "ISA 44"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 44:1"}, "Yet listen now, Yaqub my servant, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and Israel, whom I have chosen. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 44:2"}, "This is what the LORD who made you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and formed you from the womb, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who will help you says: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cDon\u2019t be afraid, Yaqub my servant; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and you, Jeshurun, whom I have chosen. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 44:3"}, "For I will pour water on him who is thirsty, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and streams on the dry ground. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I will pour my Spirit on your descendants, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and my blessing on your offspring: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 44:4"}, "and they will spring up amongst the grass, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["as willows by the watercourses. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 44:5"}, "One will say, \u2018I am the LORD\u2019s;\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and another will be called by the name of Yaqub; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and another will write with his hand \u2018to the LORD,\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and honour the name of Israel.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 44:6"}, "This is what the LORD, the King of Israel, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his Redeemer, the LORD of Armies, says: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cI am the first, and I am the last; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and besides me there is no Allah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 44:7"}, "Who is like me? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Who will call, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will declare it, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and set it in order for me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["since I established the ancient people? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Let them declare the things that are coming, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and that will happen. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 44:8"}, "Don\u2019t fear, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["neither be afraid. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Haven\u2019t I declared it to you long ago, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and shown it? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["You are my witnesses. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Is there Allah besides me? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Indeed, there is not. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I don\u2019t know any other Rock.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 44:9"}, "Everyone who makes a carved image is vain. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The things that they delight in will not profit. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Their own witnesses don\u2019t see, nor know, that they may be disappointed.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 44:10"}, "Who has fashioned a god, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["or moulds an image that is profitable for nothing? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 44:11"}, "Behold, all his fellows will be disappointed; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the workmen are mere men. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Let them all be gathered together. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let them stand up. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They will fear. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They will be put to shame together. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 44:12"}, "The blacksmith takes an axe, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["works in the coals, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["fashions it with hammers, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and works it with his strong arm. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He is hungry, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his strength fails; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["he drinks no water, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and is faint. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 44:13"}, "The carpenter stretches out a line. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He marks it out with a pencil. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He shapes it with planes. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He marks it out with compasses, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and shapes it like the figure of a man, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["with the beauty of a man, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to reside in a house. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 44:14"}, "He cuts down cedars for himself, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and takes the cypress and the oak, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and strengthens for himself one amongst the trees of the forest.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He plants a cypress tree, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the rain nourishes it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 44:15"}, "Then it will be for a man to burn; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he takes some of it, and warms himself. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, he burns it, and bakes bread. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Yes, he makes a god, and worships it; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["he makes it a carved image, and falls down to it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 44:16"}, "He burns part of it in the fire. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["With part of it, he eats meat. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He roasts a roast, and is satisfied. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Yes, he warms himself, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and says, \u201cAha! I am warm. I have seen the fire.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 44:17"}, "The rest of it he makes into a god, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["even his engraved image. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He bows down to it and worships, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and prays to it, and says, \u201cDeliver me; for you are my god!\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 44:18"}, "They don\u2019t know, neither do they consider: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for he has shut their eyes, that they can\u2019t see; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and their hearts, that they can\u2019t understand. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 44:19"}, "No one thinks, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["neither is there knowledge nor understanding to say, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cI have burnt part of it in the fire. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, I have also baked bread on its coals. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I have roasted meat and eaten it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Shall I make the rest of it into an abomination? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Shall I bow down to a tree trunk?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 44:20"}, "He feeds on ashes. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["A deceived heart has turned him aside; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he can\u2019t deliver his soul, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor say, \u201cIsn\u2019t there a lie in my right hand?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 44:21"}, "Remember these things, Yaqub and Israel; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for you are my servant. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I have formed you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You are my servant. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Israel, you will not be forgotten by me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 44:22"}, "I have blotted out, as a thick cloud, your transgressions,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and, as a cloud, your sins. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Return to me, for I have redeemed you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 44:23"}, "Sing, you heavens, for the LORD has done it! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Shout, you lower parts of the earth! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Break out into singing, you mountains, O forest, all of your trees,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for the LORD has redeemed Yaqub, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will glorify himself in Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 44:24"}, "The LORD, your Redeemer, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he who formed you from the womb says: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cI am the LORD, who makes all things; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who alone stretches out the heavens; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who spreads out the earth by myself; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ISA 44:25"}, "who frustrates the signs of the liars, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and makes diviners mad; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["who turns wise men backward, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and makes their knowledge foolish; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ISA 44:26"}, "who confirms the word of his servant, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and performs the counsel of his messengers; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["who says of Jerusalem, \u2018She will be inhabited;\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and of the cities of Judah, \u2018They will be built,\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and \u2018I will raise up its waste places;\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "27", "sid": "ISA 44:27"}, "who says to the deep, \u2018Be dry,\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and \u2018I will dry up your rivers;\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "28", "sid": "ISA 44:28"}, "Who says of Dhul-Qarnayn, \u2018He is my shepherd, and shall perform all my pleasure,\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["even saying of Jerusalem, \u2018She will be built;\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and of the temple, \u2018Your foundation will be laid.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "45", "sid": "ISA 45"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 45:1"}, "The LORD says to his anointed, to Dhul-Qarnayn, whose right hand I have held, to subdue nations before him, and strip\nkings of their armour; to open the doors before him, and the gates shall not be shut:\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 45:2"}, "\u201cI will go before you \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and make the rough places smooth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I will break the doors of bronze in pieces \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and cut apart the bars of iron. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 45:3"}, "I will give you the treasures of darkness \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and hidden riches of secret places, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["that you may know that it is I, the LORD, who call you by your name,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["even Allah of Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 45:4"}, "For Yaqub my servant\u2019s sake, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and Israel my chosen, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I have called you by your name. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I have given you a title, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["though you have not known me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 45:5"}, "I am the LORD, and there is no one else. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Besides me, there is no Allah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I will strengthen", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["45:5 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, equip"]}], "caller": "+"}, " you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["though you have not known me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 45:6"}, "that they may know from the rising of the sun, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and from the west, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["that there is no one besides me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I am the LORD, and there is no one else. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 45:7"}, "I form the light \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and create darkness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I make peace \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and create calamity. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I am the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who does all these things. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 45:8"}, "Rain, you heavens, from above, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and let the skies pour down righteousness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Let the earth open, that it may produce salvation, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and let it cause righteousness to spring up with it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I, the LORD, have created it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 45:9"}, "Woe to him who strives with his Maker\u2014 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a clay pot amongst the clay pots of the earth! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Shall the clay ask him who fashions it, \u2018What are you making?\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["or your work, \u2018He has no hands?\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 45:10"}, "Woe to him who says to a father, \u2018What have you become the father of?\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["or to a mother, \u2018What have you given birth to?\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 45:11"}, "The LORD, the Holy One of Israel \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his Maker says: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cYou ask me about the things that are to come, concerning my sons,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and you command me concerning the work of my hands! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 45:12"}, "I have made the earth, and created man on it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I, even my hands, have stretched out the heavens. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I have commanded all their army. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 45:13"}, "I have raised him up in righteousness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I will make all his ways straight. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He shall build my city, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he shall let my exiles go free, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["not for price nor reward,\u201d says the LORD of Armies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 45:14"}, "The LORD says: \u201cThe labour of Egypt, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the merchandise of Ethiopia, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the Sabeans, men of stature, will come over to you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and they will be yours. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They will go after you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They shall come over in chains. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They will bow down to you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They will make supplication to you: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u2018Surely Allah is in you; and there is no one else. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["There is no other god. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 45:15"}, "Most certainly you are Allah who has hidden yourself, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Allah of Israel, the Saviour.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 45:16"}, "They will be disappointed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["yes, confounded, all of them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Those who are makers of idols will go into confusion together.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 45:17"}, "Israel will be saved by the LORD with an everlasting salvation.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You will not be disappointed nor confounded to ages everlasting.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 45:18"}, "For the LORD who created the heavens, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Allah who formed the earth and made it, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who established it and didn\u2019t create it a waste, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who formed it to be inhabited says: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cI am the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["There is no other. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 45:19"}, "I have not spoken in secret, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["in a place of the land of darkness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I didn\u2019t say to the offspring of Yaqub, \u2018Seek me in vain.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I, the LORD, speak righteousness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I declare things that are right. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 45:20"}, "\u201cAssemble yourselves and come. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Draw near together, you who have escaped from the nations. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Those have no knowledge who carry the wood of their engraved image,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and pray to a god that can\u2019t save. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 45:21"}, "Declare and present it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, let them take counsel together. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Who has shown this from ancient time? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Who has declared it of old? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Haven\u2019t I, the LORD? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["There is no other Allah besides me, a just Allah and a Saviour.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["There is no one besides me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 45:22"}, "\u201cLook to me, and be saved, all the ends of the earth; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for I am Allah, and there is no other. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 45:23"}, "I have sworn by myself. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The word has gone out of my mouth in righteousness, and will not be revoked,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["that to me every knee shall bow, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["every tongue shall take an oath. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 45:24"}, "They will say of me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u2018There is righteousness and strength only in the LORD.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Even to him will men come. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["All those who raged against him will be disappointed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ISA 45:25"}, "All the offspring of Israel will be justified in the LORD,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will rejoice! \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "46", "sid": "ISA 46"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 46:1"}, "Bel bows down. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Nebo stoops. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Their idols are carried by animals, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and on the livestock. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["The things that you carried around are heavy loads, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a burden for the weary. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 46:2"}, "They stoop and they bow down together. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They could not deliver the burden, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but they have gone into captivity. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 46:3"}, "\u201cListen to me, house of Yaqub, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and all the remnant of the house of Israel, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that have been carried from their birth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that have been carried from the womb. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 46:4"}, "Even to old age I am he, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and even to grey hairs I will carry you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I have made, and I will bear. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, I will carry, and will deliver. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 46:5"}, "\u201cTo whom will you compare me, and consider my equal, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and compare me, as if we were the same? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 46:6"}, "Some pour out gold from the bag, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and weigh silver in the balance. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They hire a goldsmith, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he makes it a god. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They fall down\u2014 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["yes, they worship. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 46:7"}, "They bear it on their shoulder. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They carry it, and set it in its place, and it stands there.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["It cannot move from its place. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Yes, one may cry to it, yet it can not answer. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["It cannot save him out of his trouble. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 46:8"}, "\u201cRemember this, and show yourselves men. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Bring it to mind again, you transgressors. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 46:9"}, "Remember the former things of old: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for I am Allah, and there is no other. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I am Allah, and there is none like me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 46:10"}, "I declare the end from the beginning, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and from ancient times things that are not yet done. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I say: My counsel will stand, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I will do all that I please. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 46:11"}, "I call a ravenous bird from the east, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the man of my counsel from a far country. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Yes, I have spoken. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will also bring it to pass. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I have planned. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will also do it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 46:12"}, "Listen to me, you stubborn-hearted, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who are far from righteousness! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 46:13"}, "I bring my righteousness near. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["It is not far off, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and my salvation will not wait. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I will grant salvation to Zion, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["my glory to Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "47", "sid": "ISA 47"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 47:1"}, "\u201cCome down, and sit in the dust, virgin daughter of Babylon.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Sit on the ground without a throne, daughter of the Chaldeans.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["For you will no longer be called tender and delicate. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 47:2"}, "Take the millstones, and grind flour. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Remove your veil, lift up your skirt, uncover your legs, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and wade through the rivers. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 47:3"}, "Your nakedness will be uncovered. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, your shame will be seen. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I will take vengeance, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will spare no one.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 47:4"}, "Our Redeemer, the LORD of Armies is his name, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["is the Holy One of Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 47:5"}, "\u201cSit in silence, and go into darkness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["daughter of the Chaldeans. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["For you shall no longer be called \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the mistress of kingdoms. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 47:6"}, "I was angry with my people. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I profaned my inheritance, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and gave them into your hand. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["You showed them no mercy. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You laid a very heavy yoke on the aged. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 47:7"}, "You said, \u2018I will be a princess forever;\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so that you didn\u2019t lay these things to your heart, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor did you remember the results. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 47:8"}, "\u201cNow therefore hear this, you who are given to pleasures, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who sit securely, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["who say in your heart, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u2018I am, and there is no one else besides me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I shall not sit as a widow, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["neither shall I know the loss of children.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 47:9"}, "But these two things shall come to you in a moment in one day,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the loss of children and widowhood. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They will come on you in their full measure, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["in the multitude of your sorceries, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the great abundance of your enchantments. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 47:10"}, "For you have trusted in your wickedness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You have said, \u2018No one sees me.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Your wisdom and your knowledge has perverted you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You have said in your heart, \u2018I am, and there is no one else besides me.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 47:11"}, "Therefore disaster will come on you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You won\u2019t know when it dawns. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Mischief will fall on you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You won\u2019t be able to put it away. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Desolation will come on you suddenly, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["which you don\u2019t understand. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 47:12"}, "\u201cStand now with your enchantments, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and with the multitude of your sorceries, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["in which you have laboured from your youth; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["as if you might profit; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["as if you might prevail. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 47:13"}, "You are wearied in the multitude of your counsels. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Now let the astrologers, the stargazers, and the monthly prognosticators, stand up and save you from the things that will\ncome on you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 47:14"}, "Behold, they are like stubble. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The fire will burn them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They won\u2019t deliver themselves from the power of the flame. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["It won\u2019t be a coal to warm at \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["or a fire to sit by. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 47:15"}, "The things that you laboured in will be like this: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["those who have trafficked with you from your youth will each wander in his own way.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["There will be no one to save you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "48", "sid": "ISA 48"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 48:1"}, "\u201cHear this, house of Yaqub, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["you who are called by the name of Israel, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and have come out of the waters of Judah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["You swear by the LORD\u2019s name, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and make mention of Allah of Israel, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but not in truth, nor in righteousness \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 48:2"}, "(for they call themselves citizens of the holy city, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and rely on Allah of Israel; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the LORD of Armies is his name): \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 48:3"}, "I have declared the former things from of old; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["yes, they went out of my mouth, and I revealed them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I did them suddenly, and they happened. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 48:4"}, "Because I knew that you are obstinate, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your neck is an iron sinew, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your brow bronze; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 48:5"}, "therefore I have declared it to you from of old; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["before it came to pass I showed it to you; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["lest you should say, \u2018My idol has done them, and my engraved image, and my molten image, has commanded them.\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 48:6"}, "You have heard it; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["see all this. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["And you, won\u2019t you declare it? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cI have shown you new things from this time, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["even hidden things, which you have not known. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 48:7"}, "They are created now, and not from of old; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and before today you didn\u2019t hear them; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["lest you should say, \u2018Behold, I knew them.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 48:8"}, "Yes, you didn\u2019t hear; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["yes, you didn\u2019t know; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["yes, from of old your ear was not opened: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for I knew that you dealt very treacherously, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and were called a transgressor from the womb. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 48:9"}, "For my name\u2019s sake, I will defer my anger, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and for my praise I hold it back for you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so that I don\u2019t cut you off. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 48:10"}, "Behold, I have refined you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but not as silver. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I have chosen you in the furnace of affliction. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 48:11"}, "For my own sake, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for my own sake, I will do it; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for how would my name be profaned? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will not give my glory to another. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 48:12"}, "\u201cListen to me, O Yaqub, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and Israel my called: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I am he; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I am the first, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I am also the last. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 48:13"}, "Yes, my hand has laid the foundation of the earth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and my right hand has spread out the heavens. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["when I call to them, they stand up together. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 48:14"}, "\u201cAssemble yourselves, all of you, and hear; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who amongst them has declared these things? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He whom the LORD loves will do what he likes to Babylon, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his arm will be against the Chaldeans. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 48:15"}, "I, even I, have spoken; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["yes, I have called him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I have brought him, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he shall make his way prosperous. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 48:16"}, "\u201cCome near to me and hear this: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cFrom the beginning I have not spoken in secret; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["from the time that it happened, I was there.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Now the Lord ALLAH has sent me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["with his Spirit. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 48:17"}, "The LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["your Redeemer, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the Holy One of Israel says: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cI am Allah your LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who teaches you to profit, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who leads you by the way that you should go. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 48:18"}, "Oh that you had listened to my commandments! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Then your peace would have been like a river, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your righteousness like the waves of the sea. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 48:19"}, "Your offspring also would have been as the sand, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the descendants of your body like its grains. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["His name would not be cut off nor destroyed from before me.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 48:20"}, "Leave Babylon! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Flee from the Chaldeans! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["With a voice of singing announce this, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["tell it even to the end of the earth: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["say, \u201cThe LORD has redeemed his servant Yaqub!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 48:21"}, "They didn\u2019t thirst when he led them through the deserts. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He caused the waters to flow out of the rock for them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He split the rock also, and the waters gushed out. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 48:22"}, "\u201cThere is no peace\u201d, says the LORD, \u201cfor the wicked.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "49", "sid": "ISA 49"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 49:1"}, "Listen, islands, to me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Listen, you peoples, from afar: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["the LORD has called me from the womb; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["from the inside of my mother he has mentioned my name. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 49:2"}, "He has made my mouth like a sharp sword. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He has hidden me in the shadow of his hand. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He has made me a polished shaft. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He has kept me close in his quiver. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 49:3"}, "He said to me, \u201cYou are my servant; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Israel, in whom I will be glorified.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 49:4"}, "But I said, \u201cI have laboured in vain. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I have spent my strength in vain for nothing; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["yet surely the justice due to me is with the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and my reward with my Allah.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 49:5"}, "Now the LORD says, he who formed me from the womb to be his servant,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to bring Yaqub again to him, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and to gather Israel to him, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for I am honourable in the LORD\u2019s eyes, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and my Allah has become my strength. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 49:6"}, "Indeed, he says, \u201cIt is too light a thing that you should be my servant to raise up the tribes of Yaqub,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and to restore the preserved of Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I will also give you as a light to the nations, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that you may be my salvation to the end of the earth.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 49:7"}, "The LORD, the Redeemer of Israel, and his Holy One, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["says to him whom man despises, to him whom the nation abhors, to a servant of rulers:\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cKings shall see and rise up; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["princes, and they shall worship; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["because of the LORD who is faithful, even the Holy One of Israel, who has chosen you.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 49:8"}, "The LORD says, \u201cIn an acceptable time I have answered you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and in a day of salvation I have helped you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I will preserve you, and give you for a covenant of the people,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to raise up the land, to make them inherit the desolate heritage,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 49:9"}, "saying to those who are bound, \u2018Come out!\u2019; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to those who are in darkness, \u2018Show yourselves!\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cThey shall feed along the paths, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and their pasture shall be on all treeless heights. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 49:10"}, "They shall not hunger nor thirst; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["neither shall the heat nor sun strike them: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for he who has mercy on them will lead them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will guide them by springs of water. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 49:11"}, "I will make all my mountains a road, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and my highways shall be exalted. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 49:12"}, "Behold, these shall come from afar; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and behold, these from the north and from the west; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and these from the land of Sinim.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 49:13"}, "Sing, heavens; and be joyful, earth; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and break out into singing, mountains: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for the LORD has comforted his people, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will have compassion on his afflicted. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 49:14"}, "But Zion said, \u201cThe LORD has forsaken me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the Lord has forgotten me.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 49:15"}, "\u201cCan a woman forget her nursing child, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that she should not have compassion on the son of her womb? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Yes, these may forget, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["yet I will not forget you! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 49:16"}, "Behold, I have engraved you on the palms of my hands. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Your walls are continually before me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 49:17"}, "Your children hurry. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Your destroyers and those who devastated you will leave you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 49:18"}, "Lift up your eyes all around, and see: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["all these gather themselves together, and come to you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["As I live,\u201d says the LORD, \u201cyou shall surely clothe yourself with them all as with an ornament,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and dress yourself with them, like a bride. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 49:19"}, "\u201cFor, as for your waste and your desolate places, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your land that has been destroyed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["surely now that land will be too small for the inhabitants, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and those who swallowed you up will be far away. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 49:20"}, "The children of your bereavement will say in your ears, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u2018This place is too small for me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Give me a place to live in.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 49:21"}, "Then you will say in your heart, \u2018Who has conceived these for me, since I have been bereaved of my children,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and am solitary, an exile, and wandering back and forth? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Who has brought these up? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Behold, I was left alone. Where were these?\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 49:22"}, "The Lord ALLAH says, \u201cBehold, I will lift up my hand to the nations,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and lift up my banner to the peoples; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["and they shall bring your sons in their bosom, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your daughters shall be carried on their shoulders. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 49:23"}, "Kings shall be your foster fathers, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and their queens your nursing mothers. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They will bow down to you with their faces to the earth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and lick the dust of your feet; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Then you will know that I am the LORD; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and those who wait for me shall not be disappointed.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 49:24"}, "Shall the plunder be taken from the mighty, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["or the lawful captives be delivered? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ISA 49:25"}, "But the LORD says, \u201cEven the captives of the mighty shall be taken away,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the plunder retrieved from the fierce; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for I will contend with him who contends with you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I will save your children. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "26", "sid": "ISA 49:26"}, "I will feed those who oppress you with their own flesh; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and they will be drunk on their own blood, as with sweet wine.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Then all flesh shall know that I, the LORD, am your Saviour,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your Redeemer, the Mighty One of Yaqub.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "50", "sid": "ISA 50"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 50:1"}, "The LORD says, \u201cWhere is the bill of your mother\u2019s divorce, with which I have put her away?\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["or to which of my creditors have I sold you? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Behold, you were sold for your iniquities, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your mother was put away for your transgressions. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 50:2"}, "Why, when I came, was there no one? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["when I called, why was there no one to answer? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Is my hand shortened at all, that it can\u2019t redeem? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["or have I no power to deliver? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Behold, at my rebuke I dry up the sea. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I make the rivers a wilderness: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["their fish stink, because there is no water, and die for thirst.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 50:3"}, "I clothe the heavens with blackness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I make sackcloth their covering.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 50:4"}, "The Lord ALLAH has given me the tongue of those who are taught,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that I may know how to sustain with words him who is weary. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He wakens morning by morning, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["he wakens my ear to hear as those who are taught. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 50:5"}, "The Lord ALLAH has opened my ear, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I was not rebellious. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I have not turned back. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 50:6"}, "I gave my back to those who beat me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and my cheeks to those who plucked off the hair. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I didn\u2019t hide my face from shame and spitting. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 50:7"}, "For the Lord ALLAH will help me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Therefore I have not been confounded. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Therefore I have set my face like a flint, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I know that I shall not be disappointed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 50:8"}, "He who justifies me is near. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Who will bring charges against me? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Let us stand up together. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Who is my adversary? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Let him come near to me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 50:9"}, "Behold, the Lord ALLAH will help me! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Who is he who will condemn me? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Behold, they will all grow old like a garment. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The moths will eat them up. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 50:10"}, "Who amongst you fears the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and obeys the voice of his servant? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He who walks in darkness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and has no light, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["let him trust in the LORD\u2019s name, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and rely on his Allah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 50:11"}, "Behold, all you who kindle a fire, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who adorn yourselves with torches around yourselves; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["walk in the flame of your fire, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and amongst the torches that you have kindled. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["You will have this from my hand: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["You will lie down in sorrow. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "51", "sid": "ISA 51"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 51:1"}, "\u201cListen to me, you who follow after righteousness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["you who seek the LORD: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["look to the rock you were cut from, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and to the quarry you were dug from. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 51:2"}, "Look to Ibrahim your father, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and to Sarah who bore you; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for when he was but one I called him, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I blessed him, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and made him many. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 51:3"}, "For the LORD has comforted Zion. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He has comforted all her waste places, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and has made her wilderness like Eden, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and her desert like the garden of the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Joy and gladness will be found therein, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["thanksgiving, and the voice of melody. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 51:4"}, "\u201cListen to me, my people; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and hear me, my nation: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for a law will go out from me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I will establish my justice for a light to the peoples. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 51:5"}, "My righteousness is near. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["My salvation has gone out, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and my arms will judge the peoples. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["The islands will wait for me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and they will trust my arm. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 51:6"}, "Lift up your eyes to the heavens, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and look on the earth beneath; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for the heavens will vanish away like smoke, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the earth will wear out like a garment; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and its inhabitants will die in the same way: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["but my salvation will be forever, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and my righteousness will not be abolished. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 51:7"}, "\u201cListen to me, you who know righteousness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the people in whose heart is my law: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Don\u2019t fear the reproach of men, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and don\u2019t be dismayed at their insults. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 51:8"}, "For the moth will eat them up like a garment, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the worm will eat them like wool; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["but my righteousness will be forever, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and my salvation to all generations.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 51:9"}, "Awake, awake, put on strength, arm of the LORD! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Awake, as in the days of old, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the generations of ancient times. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Isn\u2019t it you who cut Rahab in pieces, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who pierced the monster? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 51:10"}, "Isn\u2019t it you who dried up the sea, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the waters of the great deep; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who made the depths of the sea a way for the redeemed to pass over?\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 51:11"}, "Those ransomed by the LORD will return, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and come with singing to Zion; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and everlasting joy shall be on their heads. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They will obtain gladness and joy. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Sorrow and sighing shall flee away. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 51:12"}, "\u201cI, even I, am he who comforts you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Who are you, that you are afraid of man who shall die, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and of the son of man who will be made as grass? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 51:13"}, "Have you forgotten the LORD your Maker, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who stretched out the heavens, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and laid the foundations of the earth? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Do you live in fear continually all day because of the fury of the oppressor,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["when he prepares to destroy? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Where is the fury of the oppressor? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 51:14"}, "The captive exile will speedily be freed; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he will not die and go down into the pit, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his bread will not fail. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 51:15"}, "For I am Allah your LORD, who stirs up the sea, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so that its waves roar: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the LORD of Armies is his name. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 51:16"}, "I have put my words in your mouth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and have covered you in the shadow of my hand, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["that I may plant the heavens, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and lay the foundations of the earth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and tell Zion, \u2018You are my people.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 51:17"}, "Awake, awake! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Stand up, Jerusalem, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["you who have drunk from the LORD\u2019s hand the cup of his wrath.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["You have drunken the bowl of the cup of staggering, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and drained it. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 51:18"}, "There is no one to guide her amongst all the sons to whom she has given birth;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and there is no one who takes her by the hand amongst all the sons who she has brought up.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 51:19"}, "These two things have happened to you\u2014 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who will grieve with you?\u2014 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["desolation and destruction, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and famine and the sword. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["How can I comfort you? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 51:20"}, "Your sons have fainted. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They lie at the head of all the streets, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["like an antelope in a net. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They are full of the LORD\u2019s wrath, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the rebuke of your Allah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 51:21"}, "Therefore now hear this, you afflicted, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and drunken, but not with wine: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 51:22"}, "Your Lord ALLAH, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["your Allah who pleads the cause of his people, says, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cBehold, I have taken out of your hand the cup of staggering,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["even the bowl of the cup of my wrath. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You will not drink it any more: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 51:23"}, "and I will put it into the hand of those who afflict you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who have said to your soul, \u2018Bow down, that we may walk over you;\u2019\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and you have laid your back as the ground, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["like a street to those who walk over.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "52", "sid": "ISA 52"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 52:1"}, "Awake, awake! Put on your strength, Zion. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Put on your beautiful garments, Jerusalem, the holy city: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for from now on the uncircumcised and the unclean will no more come into you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 52:2"}, "Shake yourself from the dust! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Arise, sit up, Jerusalem! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Release yourself from the bonds of your neck, captive daughter of Zion!\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 52:3"}, "For the LORD says, \u201cYou were sold for nothing; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and you will be redeemed without money.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 52:4"}, "For the Lord ALLAH says: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cMy people went down at the first into Egypt to live there: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the Assyrian has oppressed them without cause. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 52:5"}, "\u201cNow therefore, what do I do here,\u201d says the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cseeing that my people are taken away for nothing? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Those who rule over them mock,\u201d says the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cand my name is blasphemed continually all day long. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 52:6"}, "Therefore my people shall know my name. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Therefore they shall know in that day that I am he who speaks.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Behold, it is I.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 52:7"}, "How beautiful on the mountains are the feet of him who brings good news,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who publishes peace, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who brings good news, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who proclaims salvation, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who says to Zion, \u201cYour Allah reigns!\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 52:8"}, "Your watchmen lift up their voice, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["together they sing; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for they shall see eye to eye, when the LORD returns to Zion.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 52:9"}, "Break out into joy, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["sing together, you waste places of Jerusalem; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for the LORD has comforted his people. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He has redeemed Jerusalem. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 52:10"}, "The LORD has made bare his holy arm in the eyes of all the nations;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and all the ends of the earth have seen the salvation of our Allah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 52:11"}, "Depart, depart, go out from there; touch no unclean thing!\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Go out from amongst her! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Cleanse yourselves, you who carry the LORD\u2019s vessels. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 52:12"}, "For you shall not go out in haste, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["neither shall you go by flight: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for the LORD will go before you; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and Allah of Israel will be your rear guard. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 52:13"}, "Behold, my servant will deal wisely. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will be exalted and lifted up, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will be very high. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 52:14"}, "Just as many were astonished at you \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["(his appearance was marred more than any man, and his form more than the sons of men),\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 52:15"}, "so he will cleanse", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["52:15 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["or, sprinkle"]}], "caller": "+"}, " many nations.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Kings will shut their mouths at him: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for they will see that which had not been told them; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and they will understand that which they had not heard. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "53", "sid": "ISA 53"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 53:1"}, "Who has believed our message? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["To whom has the arm of the LORD been revealed? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 53:2"}, "For he grew up before him as a tender plant, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and as a root out of dry ground. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He has no good looks or majesty. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["When we see him, there is no beauty that we should desire him.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 53:3"}, "He was despised, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and rejected by men; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["a man of suffering, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and acquainted with disease. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He was despised as one from whom men hide their face; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and we didn\u2019t respect him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 53:4"}, "Surely he has borne our sickness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and carried our suffering; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["yet we considered him plagued, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["struck by Allah, and afflicted. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 53:5"}, "But he was pierced for our transgressions. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He was crushed for our iniquities. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["The punishment that brought our peace was on him; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and by his wounds we are healed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 53:6"}, "All we like sheep have gone astray. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Everyone has turned to his own way; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the LORD has laid on him the iniquity of us all. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 53:7"}, "He was oppressed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["yet when he was afflicted he didn\u2019t open his mouth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["As a lamb that is led to the slaughter, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and as a sheep that before its shearers is silent, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so he didn\u2019t open his mouth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 53:8"}, "He was taken away by oppression and judgement; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and as for his generation, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who considered that he was cut off out of the land of the living\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and stricken for the disobedience of my people? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 53:9"}, "They made his grave with the wicked, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and with a rich man in his death; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["although he had done no violence, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor was any deceit in his mouth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 53:10"}, "Yet it pleased the LORD to bruise him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He has caused him to suffer. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["When you make his soul an offering for sin, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["he will see his offspring. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He will prolong his days, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the LORD\u2019s pleasure will prosper in his hand. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 53:11"}, "After the suffering of his soul, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["he will see the light", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["53:11 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["So read the Dead Sea Scrolls and Septuagint. Masoretic Text omits \u201cthe\nlight\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " and be satisfied. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["My righteous servant will justify many by the knowledge of himself;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he will bear their iniquities. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 53:12"}, "Therefore I will give him a portion with the great, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he will divide the plunder with the strong; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["because he poured out his soul to death, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and was counted with the transgressors; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["yet he bore the sins of many, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and made intercession for the transgressors. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "54", "sid": "ISA 54"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 54:1"}, "\u201cSing, barren, you who didn\u2019t give birth; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["break out into singing, and cry aloud, you who didn\u2019t travail with child:\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for more are the children of the desolate than the children of the married wife,\u201d says the LORD.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 54:2"}, "\u201cEnlarge the place of your tent, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and let them stretch out the curtains of your habitations; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["don\u2019t spare: lengthen your cords, and strengthen your stakes.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 54:3"}, "For you will spread out on the right hand and on the left; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your offspring will possess the nations, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and settle in desolate cities. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 54:4"}, "\u201cDon\u2019t be afraid; for you will not be ashamed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Don\u2019t be confounded; for you will not be disappointed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["For you will forget the shame of your youth; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the reproach of your widowhood you shall remember no more.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 54:5"}, "For your Maker is your husband; the LORD of Armies is his name.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The Holy One of Israel is your Redeemer. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He will be called Allah of the whole earth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 54:6"}, "For the LORD has called you as a wife forsaken and grieved in spirit,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["even a wife of youth, when she is cast off,\u201d says your Allah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 54:7"}, "\u201cFor a small moment I have forsaken you; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but I will gather you with great mercies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 54:8"}, "In overflowing wrath I hid my face from you for a moment; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but with everlasting loving kindness I will have mercy on you,\u201d says the LORD your Redeemer.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 54:9"}, "\u201cFor this is like the waters of Nuh to me; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for as I have sworn that the waters of Nuh will no more go over the earth,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so I have sworn that I will not be angry with you, nor rebuke you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 54:10"}, "For the mountains may depart, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the hills be removed; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["but my loving kindness will not depart from you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and my covenant of peace will not be removed,\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["says the LORD who has mercy on you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 54:11"}, "\u201cYou afflicted, tossed with storms, and not comforted, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["behold, I will set your stones in beautiful colours, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and lay your foundations with sapphires. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 54:12"}, "I will make your pinnacles of rubies, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["your gates of sparkling jewels, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and all your walls of precious stones. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 54:13"}, "All your children will be taught by the LORD; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your children\u2019s peace will be great. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 54:14"}, "In righteousness you will be established. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You will be far from oppression, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for you will not be afraid; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and far from terror, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for it shall not come near you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 54:15"}, "Behold, they may gather together, but not by me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Whoever gathers together against you will fall because of you.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 54:16"}, "\u201cBehold, I have created the blacksmith who fans the coals into flame,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and forges a weapon for his work; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I have created the destroyer to destroy. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 54:17"}, "No weapon that is formed against you will prevail; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and you will condemn every tongue that rises against you in judgement.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["This is the heritage of the LORD\u2019s servants, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and their righteousness is of me,\u201d says the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "55", "sid": "ISA 55"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 55:1"}, "\u201cHey! Come, everyone who thirsts, to the waters! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Come, he who has no money, buy, and eat! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, come, buy wine and milk without money and without price.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 55:2"}, "Why do you spend money for that which is not bread, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your labour for that which doesn\u2019t satisfy? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Listen diligently to me, and eat that which is good, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and let your soul delight itself in richness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 55:3"}, "Turn your ear, and come to me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Hear, and your soul will live: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I will make an everlasting covenant with you, even the sure mercies of Dawood.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 55:4"}, "Behold, I have given him for a witness to the peoples, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a leader and commander to the peoples. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 55:5"}, "Behold, you shall call a nation that you don\u2019t know; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a nation that didn\u2019t know you shall run to you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["because of Allah your LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and for the Holy One of Israel; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for he has glorified you.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 55:6"}, "Seek the LORD while he may be found. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Call on him while he is near. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 55:7"}, "Let the wicked forsake his way, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the unrighteous man his thoughts. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Let him return to the LORD, and he will have mercy on him; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and to our Allah, for he will freely pardon. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 55:8"}, "\u201cFor my thoughts are not your thoughts, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your ways are not my ways,\u201d says the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 55:9"}, "\u201cFor as the heavens are higher than the earth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so are my ways higher than your ways, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and my thoughts than your thoughts. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 55:10"}, "For as the rain comes down and the snow from the sky, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and doesn\u2019t return there, but waters the earth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and makes it grow and bud, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and gives seed to the sower and bread to the eater; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 55:11"}, "so is my word that goes out of my mouth: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["it will not return to me void, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but it will accomplish that which I please, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and it will prosper in the thing I sent it to do. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 55:12"}, "For you shall go out with joy, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and be led out with peace. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["The mountains and the hills will break out before you into singing;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and all the trees of the fields will clap their hands. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 55:13"}, "Instead of the thorn the cypress tree will come up; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and instead of the brier the myrtle tree will come up: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["and it will make a name for the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for an everlasting sign that will not be cut off.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "56", "sid": "ISA 56"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 56:1"}, "The LORD says, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cMaintain justice, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and do what is right; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for my salvation is near, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and my righteousness will soon be revealed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 56:2"}, "Blessed is the man who does this, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the son of man who holds it fast; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["who keeps the Sabbath without profaning it, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and keeps his hand from doing any evil.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 56:3"}, "Let no foreigner, who has joined himself to the LORD, speak, saying,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cThe LORD will surely separate me from his people.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Do not let the eunuch say, \u201cBehold, I am a dry tree.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 56:4"}, "For the LORD says, \u201cTo the eunuchs who keep my Sabbaths, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and choose the things that please me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and hold fast to my covenant: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 56:5"}, "I will give them in my house and within my walls a memorial and a name better than of sons and of daughters.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will give them an everlasting name, that will not be cut off.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 56:6"}, "Also the foreigners who join themselves to the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to serve him, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["and to love the LORD\u2019s name, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to be his servants, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["everyone who keeps the Sabbath from profaning it, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and holds fast my covenant; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 56:7"}, "I will bring these to my holy mountain, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and make them joyful in my house of prayer. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Their burnt offerings and their sacrifices will be accepted on my altar;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for my house will be called a house of prayer for all peoples.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 56:8"}, "The Lord ALLAH, who gathers the outcasts of Israel, says, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cI will yet gather others to him, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["in addition to his own who are gathered.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 56:9"}, "All you animals of the field, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["come to devour, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["all you animals in the forest. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 56:10"}, "His watchmen are blind. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They are all without knowledge. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They are all mute dogs. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They can\u2019t bark; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["dreaming, lying down, loving to slumber. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 56:11"}, "Yes, the dogs are greedy. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They can never have enough. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They are shepherds who can\u2019t understand. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They have all turned to their own way, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["each one to his gain, from every quarter. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 56:12"}, "\u201cCome,\u201d say they, \u201cI will get wine, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and we will fill ourselves with strong drink; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and tomorrow will be as today, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["great beyond measure.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "57", "sid": "ISA 57"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 57:1"}, "The righteous perish, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and no one lays it to heart. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Merciful men are taken away, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and no one considers that the righteous is taken away from the evil.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 57:2"}, "He enters into peace. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They rest in their beds, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["each one who walks in his uprightness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 57:3"}, "\u201cBut draw near here, you sons of a sorceress, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["you offspring of adulterers and prostitutes. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 57:4"}, "Whom do you mock? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Against whom do you make a wide mouth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and stick out your tongue? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Aren\u2019t you children of disobedience, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and offspring of falsehood, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 57:5"}, "you who inflame yourselves amongst the oaks, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["under every green tree; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["who kill the children in the valleys, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["under the clefts of the rocks? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 57:6"}, "Amongst the smooth stones of the valley is your portion; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["they, they are your lot. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["You have even poured a drink offering to them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You have offered an offering. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Shall I be appeased for these things? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 57:7"}, "On a high and lofty mountain you have set your bed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You also went up there to offer sacrifice. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 57:8"}, "You have set up your memorial behind the doors and the posts;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for you have exposed yourself to someone besides me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and have gone up; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["you have enlarged your bed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and made you a covenant with them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You loved what you saw on their bed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 57:9"}, "You went to the king with oil, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and increased your perfumes, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["and sent your ambassadors far off, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and degraded yourself even to Sheol.", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["57:9 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Sheol is the place of the\ndead."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 57:10"}, "You were wearied with the length of your ways; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["yet you didn\u2019t say, \u2018It is in vain.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["You found a reviving of your strength; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["therefore you weren\u2019t faint. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 57:11"}, "\u201cWhom have you dreaded and feared, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so that you lie, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and have not remembered me, nor laid it to your heart? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Haven\u2019t I held my peace for a long time, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and you don\u2019t fear me? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 57:12"}, "I will declare your righteousness; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and as for your works, they will not benefit you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 57:13"}, "When you cry, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["let those whom you have gathered deliver you; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["but the wind will take them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a breath will carry them all away: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["but he who takes refuge in me will possess the land, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will inherit my holy mountain.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 57:14"}, "He will say, \u201cBuild up, build up, prepare the way! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Remove the stumbling-block out of the way of my people.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 57:15"}, "For the high and lofty One who inhabits eternity, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["whose name is Holy, says: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cI dwell in the high and holy place, with him also who is of a contrite and humble spirit,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to revive the spirit of the humble, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and to revive the heart of the contrite. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 57:16"}, "For I will not contend forever, neither will I always be angry;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for the spirit would faint before me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the souls whom I have made. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 57:17"}, "I was angry because of the iniquity of his covetousness, and struck him;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I hid myself and was angry; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he went on backsliding in the way of his heart. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 57:18"}, "I have seen his ways, and will heal him: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will lead him also, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and restore comforts to him and to his mourners. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 57:19"}, "I create the fruit of the lips: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Peace, peace, to him who is far off and to him who is near,\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["says the LORD; \u201cand I will heal them.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 57:20"}, "But the wicked are like the troubled sea; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for it can\u2019t rest, and its waters cast up mire and mud. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 57:21"}, "\u201cThere is no peace\u201d, says my Allah, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cfor the wicked.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "58", "sid": "ISA 58"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 58:1"}, "\u201cCry aloud, don\u2019t spare. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Lift up your voice like a trumpet. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Declare to my people their disobedience, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and to the house of Yaqub their sins. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 58:2"}, "Yet they seek me daily, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and delight to know my ways. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["As a nation that did righteousness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and didn\u2019t forsake the ordinance of their Allah, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["they ask of me righteous judgements. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They delight to draw near to Allah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 58:3"}, "\u2018Why have we fasted,\u2019 they say, \u2018and you don\u2019t see? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Why have we afflicted our soul, and you don\u2019t notice?\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cBehold, in the day of your fast you find pleasure, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and oppress all your labourers. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 58:4"}, "Behold, you fast for strife and contention, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and to strike with the fist of wickedness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You don\u2019t fast today so as to make your voice to be heard on high.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 58:5"}, "Is this the fast that I have chosen? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["A day for a man to humble his soul? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Is it to bow down his head like a reed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and to spread sackcloth and ashes under himself? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Will you call this a fast, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and an acceptable day to the LORD? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 58:6"}, "\u201cIsn\u2019t this the fast that I have chosen: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to release the bonds of wickedness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to undo the straps of the yoke, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to let the oppressed go free, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and that you break every yoke? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 58:7"}, "Isn\u2019t it to distribute your bread to the hungry, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and that you bring the poor who are cast out to your house? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["When you see the naked, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that you cover him; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and that you not hide yourself from your own flesh? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 58:8"}, "Then your light will break out as the morning, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your healing will appear quickly; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["then your righteousness shall go before you; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the LORD\u2019s glory will be your rear guard. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 58:9"}, "Then you will call, and the LORD will answer; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["you will cry for help, and he will say, \u2018Here I am.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cIf you take away from amongst you the yoke, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["finger pointing, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and speaking wickedly; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 58:10"}, "and if you pour out your soul to the hungry, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and satisfy the afflicted soul: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["then your light will rise in darkness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your obscurity will be as the noonday; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 58:11"}, "and the LORD will guide you continually, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and satisfy your soul in dry places, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and make your bones strong; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["and you shall be like a watered garden, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and like a spring of water, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["whose waters don\u2019t fail. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 58:12"}, "Those who shall be of you shall build the old waste places;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["you shall raise up the foundations of many generations; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["and you shall be called Repairer of the Breach, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Restorer of Paths with Dwellings. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 58:13"}, "\u201cIf you turn away your foot from the Sabbath, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["from doing your pleasure on my holy day; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["and call the Sabbath a delight, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the holy of the LORD honourable; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and shall honour it, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["not doing your own ways, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor finding your own pleasure, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor speaking your own words: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 58:14"}, "then you shall delight yourself in the LORD; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I will make you to ride on the high places of the earth;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I will feed you with the heritage of Yaqub your father:\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for the LORD\u2019s mouth has spoken it. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "59", "sid": "ISA 59"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 59:1"}, "Behold, the LORD\u2019s hand is not shortened, that it can\u2019t save;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor his ear dull, that it can\u2019t hear. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 59:2"}, "But your iniquities have separated you and your Allah, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your sins have hidden his face from you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so that he will not hear. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 59:3"}, "For your hands are defiled with blood, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your fingers with iniquity. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Your lips have spoken lies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Your tongue mutters wickedness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 59:4"}, "No one sues in righteousness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and no one pleads in truth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They trust in vanity, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and speak lies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They conceive mischief, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and give birth to iniquity. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 59:5"}, "They hatch adders\u2019 eggs, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and weave the spider\u2019s web. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He who eats of their eggs dies; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and that which is crushed breaks out into a viper. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 59:6"}, "Their webs won\u2019t become garments. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They won\u2019t cover themselves with their works. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Their works are works of iniquity, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and acts of violence are in their hands. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 59:7"}, "Their feet run to evil, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and they hurry to shed innocent blood. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Their thoughts are thoughts of iniquity. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Desolation and destruction are in their paths. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 59:8"}, "They don\u2019t know the way of peace; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and there is no justice in their ways. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They have made crooked paths for themselves; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["whoever goes in them doesn\u2019t know peace. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 59:9"}, "Therefore justice is far from us, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and righteousness doesn\u2019t overtake us. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["We look for light, but see darkness; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for brightness, but we walk in obscurity. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 59:10"}, "We grope for the wall like the blind. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Yes, we grope as those who have no eyes. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["We stumble at noon as if it were twilight. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Amongst those who are strong, we are like dead men. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 59:11"}, "We all roar like bears, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and moan bitterly like doves. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["We look for justice, but there is none; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for salvation, but it is far off from us. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 59:12"}, "For our transgressions are multiplied before you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and our sins testify against us; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for our transgressions are with us, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and as for our iniquities, we know them: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 59:13"}, "transgressing and denying the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and turning away from following our Allah, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["speaking oppression and revolt, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["conceiving and uttering from the heart words of falsehood. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 59:14"}, "Justice is turned away backward, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and righteousness stands far away; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for truth has fallen in the street, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and uprightness can\u2019t enter. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 59:15"}, "Yes, truth is lacking; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he who departs from evil makes himself a prey. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["The LORD saw it, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and it displeased him that there was no justice. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 59:16"}, "He saw that there was no man, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and wondered that there was no intercessor. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Therefore his own arm brought salvation to him; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his righteousness sustained him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 59:17"}, "He put on righteousness as a breastplate, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a helmet of salvation on his head. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He put on garments of vengeance for clothing, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and was clad with zeal as a mantle. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 59:18"}, "According to their deeds, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["he will repay as appropriate, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["wrath to his adversaries, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["recompense to his enemies; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["he will repay the islands their due. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 59:19"}, "So they will fear the LORD\u2019s name from the west, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his glory from the rising of the sun; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for he will come as a rushing stream, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["which the LORD\u2019s breath drives. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 59:20"}, "\u201cA Redeemer will come to Zion, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and to those who turn from disobedience in Yaqub,\u201d says the LORD.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 59:21"}, "\u201cAs for me, this is my covenant with them,\u201d says the LORD. \u201cMy Spirit who is on you, and my words which I have put in\nyour mouth, shall not depart out of your mouth, nor out of the mouth of your offspring, nor out of the mouth of your\noffspring\u2019s offspring,\u201d says the LORD, \u201cfrom henceforth and forever.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "60", "sid": "ISA 60"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 60:1"}, "\u201cArise, shine; for your light has come, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the LORD\u2019s glory has risen on you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 60:2"}, "For, behold, darkness will cover the earth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and thick darkness the peoples; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["but the LORD will arise on you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his glory shall be seen on you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 60:3"}, "Nations will come to your light, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and kings to the brightness of your rising. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 60:4"}, "\u201cLift up your eyes all around, and see: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["they all gather themselves together. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They come to you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Your sons will come from far away, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your daughters will be carried in arms. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 60:5"}, "Then you shall see and be radiant, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your heart will thrill and be enlarged; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["because the abundance of the sea will be turned to you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The wealth of the nations will come to you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 60:6"}, "A multitude of camels will cover you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the dromedaries of Midian and Ephah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["All from Sheba will come. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They will bring gold and frankincense, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will proclaim the praises of the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 60:7"}, "All the flocks of Kedar will be gathered together to you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The rams of Nebaioth will serve you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They will be accepted as offerings on my altar; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I will beautify my glorious house. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 60:8"}, "\u201cWho are these who fly as a cloud, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and as the doves to their windows? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 60:9"}, "Surely the islands will wait for me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the ships of Tarshish first, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["to bring your sons from far, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["their silver and their gold with them, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for the name of Allah your LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and for the Holy One of Israel, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["because he has glorified you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 60:10"}, "\u201cForeigners will build up your walls, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and their kings will serve you: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for in my wrath I struck you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but in my favour I have had mercy on you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 60:11"}, "Your gates also shall be open continually; they shall not be shut day nor night; that men may bring to you the wealth of\nthe nations, and their kings led captive. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 60:12"}, "For that nation and kingdom that will not serve you shall perish; yes, those nations shall be utterly wasted.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 60:13"}, "\u201cThe glory of Lebanon shall come to you, the cypress tree, the pine, and the box tree together, to beautify the place of\nmy sanctuary; and I will make the place of my feet glorious. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 60:14"}, "The sons of those who afflicted you will come bowing to you;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and all those who despised you will bow themselves down at the soles of your feet.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They will call you the LORD\u2019s City, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The Zion of the Holy One of Israel. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 60:15"}, "\u201cWhereas you have been forsaken and hated, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so that no one passed through you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I will make you an eternal excellency, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a joy of many generations. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 60:16"}, "You will also drink the milk of the nations, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will nurse from royal breasts. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Then you will know that I, the LORD, am your Saviour, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["your Redeemer, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the Mighty One of Yaqub. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 60:17"}, "For bronze I will bring gold; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for iron I will bring silver; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for wood, bronze, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and for stones, iron. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I will also make peace your governor, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and righteousness your ruler. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 60:18"}, "Violence shall no more be heard in your land, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor desolation or destruction within your borders; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["but you will call your walls Salvation, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your gates Praise. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 60:19"}, "The sun will be no more your light by day; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor will the brightness of the moon give light to you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["but the LORD will be your everlasting light, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your Allah will be your glory. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 60:20"}, "Your sun will not go down any more, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor will your moon withdraw itself; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for the LORD will be your everlasting light, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the days of your mourning will end. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 60:21"}, "Then your people will all be righteous. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They will inherit the land forever, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the branch of my planting, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the work of my hands, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that I may be glorified. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 60:22"}, "The little one will become a thousand, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the small one a strong nation. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I, the LORD, will do this quickly in its time.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "61", "sid": "ISA 61"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 61:1"}, "The Lord ALLAH\u2019s Spirit is on me; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["because the LORD has anointed me to preach good news to the humble.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He has sent me to bind up the broken hearted, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to proclaim liberty to the captives, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and release to those who are bound; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 61:2"}, "to proclaim the year of the LORD\u2019s favour, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the day of vengeance of our Allah; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to comfort all who mourn; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 61:3"}, "to provide for those who mourn in Zion, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["to give to them a garland for ashes, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the oil of joy for mourning, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the garment of praise for the spirit of heaviness; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["that they may be called trees of righteousness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the planting of the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that he may be glorified. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 61:4"}, "They will rebuild the old ruins. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They will raise up the places long devastated. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They will repair the ruined cities, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that have been devastated for many generations. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 61:5"}, "Strangers will stand and feed your flocks, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and foreigners will work your fields and your vineyards. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 61:6"}, "But you will be called the LORD\u2019s priests. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Men will call you the servants of our Allah. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["You will eat the wealth of the nations, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and you will boast in their glory. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 61:7"}, "Instead of your shame you will have double. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Instead of dishonour, they will rejoice in their portion. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Therefore in their land, they will possess double. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Everlasting joy will be to them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 61:8"}, "\u201cFor I, the LORD, love justice. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I hate robbery and iniquity. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["I will give them their reward in truth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I will make an everlasting covenant with them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 61:9"}, "Their offspring will be known amongst the nations, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and their offspring amongst the peoples. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["All who see them will acknowledge them, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that they are the offspring which the LORD has blessed.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 61:10"}, "I will greatly rejoice in the LORD! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["My soul will be joyful in my Allah; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for he has clothed me with the garments of salvation. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He has covered me with the robe of righteousness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["as a bridegroom decks himself with a garland, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and as a bride adorns herself with her jewels. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 61:11"}, "For as the earth produces its bud, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and as the garden causes the things that are sown in it to spring up;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so the Lord ALLAH will cause righteousness and praise to spring up before all the nations.\n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "62", "sid": "ISA 62"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 62:1"}, "For Zion\u2019s sake I will not hold my peace, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and for Jerusalem\u2019s sake I will not rest, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["until her righteousness shines out like the dawn, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and her salvation like a burning lamp. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 62:2"}, "The nations will see your righteousness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and all kings your glory, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["and you will be called by a new name, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["which the LORD\u2018s mouth will name. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 62:3"}, "You will also be a crown of beauty in the LORD\u2018s hand, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and a royal diadem in your Allah\u2018s hand. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 62:4"}, "You will not be called Forsaken any more; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor will your land be called Desolate any more: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["but you will be called Hephzibah,", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["62:4 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Hephibah means \u201cI delight in\nher\u201d."]}], "caller": "+"}, " \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your land Beulah;", {"type": "note", "marker": "f", "content": ["  ", {"type": "char", "marker": "fr", "content": ["62:4 "]}, {"type": "char", "marker": "ft", "content": ["Beulah means \u201cmarried\u201d"]}], "caller": "+"}, "\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for the LORD delights in you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your land will be married. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 62:5"}, "For as a young man marries a virgin, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so your sons will marry you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["As a bridegroom rejoices over his bride, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so your Allah will rejoice over you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 62:6"}, "I have set watchmen on your walls, Jerusalem. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They will never be silent day nor night. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["You who call on the LORD, take no rest, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 62:7"}, "and give him no rest, until he establishes, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and until he makes Jerusalem a praise in the earth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 62:8"}, "The LORD has sworn by his right hand, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and by the arm of his strength, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cSurely I will no more give your grain to be food for your enemies;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and foreigners will not drink your new wine, for which you have laboured;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 62:9"}, "but those who have harvested it will eat it, and praise the LORD;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and those who have gathered it will drink it in the courts of my sanctuary.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 62:10"}, "Go through, go through the gates! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Prepare the way of the people! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Build up, build up the highway! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Gather out the stones! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Lift up a banner for the peoples. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 62:11"}, "Behold, the LORD has proclaimed to the end of the earth, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cSay to the daughter of Zion, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u2018Behold, your salvation comes. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Behold, his reward is with him, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his recompense before him.\u2019\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 62:12"}, "They will call them \u201cThe Holy People, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The LORD\u2019s Redeemed\u201d. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["You will be called \u201cSought Out, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["A City Not Forsaken\u201d. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "63", "sid": "ISA 63"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 63:1"}, "Who is this who comes from Edom, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["with dyed garments from Bozrah? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Who is this who is glorious in his clothing, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["marching in the greatness of his strength? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cIt is I who speak in righteousness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["mighty to save.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 63:2"}, "Why is your clothing red, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your garments like him who treads in the wine vat? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 63:3"}, "\u201cI have trodden the wine press alone; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and of the peoples, no one was with me: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Yes, I trod them in my anger, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and trampled them in my wrath. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Their lifeblood is sprinkled on my garments, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I have stained all my clothing. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 63:4"}, "For the day of vengeance was in my heart, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the year of my redeemed has come. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 63:5"}, "I looked, and there was no one to help; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["and I wondered that there was no one to uphold: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["therefore my own arm brought salvation to me; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and my own wrath upheld me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 63:6"}, "I trod down the peoples in my anger, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and made them drunk in my wrath, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and I poured out their lifeblood on the earth.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 63:7"}, "I will tell of the loving kindnesses of the LORD \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the praises of the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["according to all that the LORD has given to us, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["and the great goodness towards the house of Israel, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["which he has given to them according to his mercies, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and according to the multitude of his loving kindnesses. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 63:8"}, "For he said, \u201cSurely, they are my people, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["children who will not deal falsely;\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so he became their Saviour. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 63:9"}, "In all their affliction he was afflicted, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the angel of his presence saved them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["In his love and in his pity he redeemed them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["He bore them, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and carried them all the days of old. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 63:10"}, "But they rebelled, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and grieved his Holy Spirit. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Therefore he turned and became their enemy, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he himself fought against them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 63:11"}, "Then he remembered the days of old, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Musa and his people, saying, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cWhere is he who brought them up out of the sea with the shepherds of his flock?\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Where is he who put his Holy Spirit amongst them?\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 63:12"}, "Who caused his glorious arm to be at Musa\u2019s right hand? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Who divided the waters before them, to make himself an everlasting name?\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 63:13"}, "Who led them through the depths, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["like a horse in the wilderness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so that they didn\u2019t stumble? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 63:14"}, "As the livestock that go down into the valley, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the LORD\u2019s Spirit caused them to rest. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["So you led your people, to make yourself a glorious name. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 63:15"}, "Look down from heaven, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and see from the habitation of your holiness and of your glory.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Where are your zeal and your mighty acts? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["The yearning of your heart and your compassion is restrained towards me.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 63:16"}, "For you are our Father, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["though Ibrahim doesn\u2019t know us, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and Israel does not acknowledge us. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["You, LORD, are our Father. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Our Redeemer from everlasting is your name. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 63:17"}, "O LORD, why do you make us wander from your ways, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and harden our heart from your fear? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Return for your servants\u2019 sake, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["the tribes of your inheritance. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 63:18"}, "Your holy people possessed it but a little while. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Our adversaries have trodden down your sanctuary. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 63:19"}, "We have become like those over whom you never ruled, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["like those who were not called by your name. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "64", "sid": "ISA 64"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 64:1"}, "Oh that you would tear the heavens, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that you would come down, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that the mountains might quake at your presence. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 64:2"}, "As when fire kindles the brushwood, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the fire causes the water to boil; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Make your name known to your adversaries, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that the nations may tremble at your presence! \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 64:3"}, "When you did awesome things which we didn\u2019t look for, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["you came down, and the mountains quaked at your presence. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 64:4"}, "For from of old men have not heard, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor perceived by the ear, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor has the eye seen Allah besides you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who works for him who waits for him. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 64:5"}, "You meet him who rejoices and does righteousness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["those who remember you in your ways. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Behold, you were angry, and we sinned. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["We have been in sin for a long time. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Shall we be saved? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 64:6"}, "For we have all become like one who is unclean, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and all our righteousness is like a polluted garment. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["We all fade like a leaf; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and our iniquities, like the wind, take us away. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 64:7"}, "There is no one who calls on your name, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who stirs himself up to take hold of you; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for you have hidden your face from us, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and have consumed us by means of our iniquities. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 64:8"}, "But now, LORD, you are our Father. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["We are the clay, and you our potter. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["We all are the work of your hand. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 64:9"}, "Don\u2019t be furious, LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and don\u2019t remember iniquity forever. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Look and see, we beg you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["we are all your people. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 64:10"}, "Your holy cities have become a wilderness. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Zion has become a wilderness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Jerusalem a desolation. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 64:11"}, "Our holy and our beautiful house, where our fathers praised you,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["is burnt with fire; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and all our pleasant places are laid waste. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 64:12"}, "Will you hold yourself back for these things, LORD? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Will you keep silent, and punish us very severely? \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "65", "sid": "ISA 65"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 65:1"}, "\u201cI am enquired of by those who didn\u2019t ask. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I am found by those who didn\u2019t seek me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I said, \u2018See me, see me,\u2019 to a nation that was not called by my name.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 65:2"}, "I have spread out my hands all day to a rebellious people, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who walk in a way that is not good, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["after their own thoughts; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 65:3"}, "a people who provoke me to my face continually, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["sacrificing in gardens, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and burning incense on bricks; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 65:4"}, "who sit amongst the graves, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and spend nights in secret places; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["who eat pig\u2019s meat, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and broth of abominable things is in their vessels; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 65:5"}, "who say, \u2018Stay by yourself, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["don\u2019t come near to me, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for I am holier than you.\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["These are smoke in my nose, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a fire that burns all day. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 65:6"}, "\u201cBehold, it is written before me: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["I will not keep silence, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but will repay, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["yes, I will repay into their bosom, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 65:7"}, "your own iniquities, and the iniquities of your fathers together\u201d, says the LORD,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cwho have burnt incense on the mountains, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and blasphemed me on the hills. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Therefore I will first measure their work into their bosom.\u201d\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 65:8"}, "The LORD says, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cAs the new wine is found in the cluster, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and one says, \u2018Don\u2019t destroy it, for a blessing is in it:\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["so I will do for my servants\u2019 sake, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that I may not destroy them all. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 65:9"}, "I will bring offspring out of Yaqub, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and out of Judah an inheritor of my mountains. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["My chosen will inherit it, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and my servants will dwell there. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 65:10"}, "Sharon will be a fold of flocks, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the valley of Achor a place for herds to lie down in, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for my people who have sought me. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 65:11"}, "\u201cBut you who forsake the LORD, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who forget my holy mountain, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who prepare a table for Fortune, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and who fill up mixed wine to Destiny; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 65:12"}, "I will destine you to the sword, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and you will all bow down to the slaughter; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["because when I called, you didn\u2019t answer. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["When I spoke, you didn\u2019t listen; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["but you did that which was evil in my eyes, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and chose that in which I didn\u2019t delight.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 65:13"}, "Therefore the Lord ALLAH says, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cBehold, my servants will eat, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but you will be hungry; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["behold, my servants will drink, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but you will be thirsty. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Behold, my servants will rejoice, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but you will be disappointed; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 65:14"}, "Behold, my servants will sing for joy of heart, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but you will cry for sorrow of heart, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will wail for anguish of spirit. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 65:15"}, "You will leave your name for a curse to my chosen; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the Lord ALLAH will kill you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["He will call his servants by another name, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 65:16"}, "so that he who blesses himself in the earth will bless himself in Allah of truth;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he who swears in the earth will swear by Allah of truth;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["because the former troubles are forgotten, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and because they are hidden from my eyes. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 65:17"}, "\u201cFor, behold, I create new heavens and a new earth; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the former things will not be remembered, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor come into mind. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 65:18"}, "But be glad and rejoice forever in that which I create; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["for, behold, I create Jerusalem to be a delight, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and her people a joy. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 65:19"}, "I will rejoice in Jerusalem, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and delight in my people; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["and the voice of weeping and the voice of crying \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["will be heard in her no more. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 65:20"}, "\u201cNo more will there be an infant who only lives a few days,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor an old man who has not filled his days; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for the child will die one hundred years old, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the sinner being one hundred years old will be accursed.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 65:21"}, "They will build houses, and inhabit them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They will plant vineyards, and eat their fruit. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 65:22"}, "They will not build, and another inhabit. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["They will not plant, and another eat: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for the days of my people will be like the days of a tree, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and my chosen will long enjoy the work of their hands. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 65:23"}, "They will not labour in vain, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["nor give birth for calamity; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["for they are the offspring of the LORD\u2019s blessed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and their descendants with them. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 65:24"}, "It will happen that, before they call, I will answer; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and while they are yet speaking, I will hear. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "25", "sid": "ISA 65:25"}, "The wolf and the lamb will feed together, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the lion will eat straw like the ox. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Dust will be the serpent\u2019s food. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["They will not hurt nor destroy in all my holy mountain,\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["says the LORD. \n"]}, {"type": "chapter", "marker": "c", "number": "66", "sid": "ISA 66"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "1", "sid": "ISA 66:1"}, "The LORD says, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cHeaven is my throne, and the earth is my footstool. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["What kind of house will you build to me? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Where will I rest? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "2", "sid": "ISA 66:2"}, "For my hand has made all these things, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and so all these things came to be,\u201d says the LORD: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cbut I will look to this man, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["even to he who is poor and of a contrite spirit, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and who trembles at my word. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "3", "sid": "ISA 66:3"}, "He who kills an ox is as he who kills a man; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["he who sacrifices a lamb, as he who breaks a dog\u2019s neck; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["he who offers an offering, as he who offers pig\u2019s blood; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["he who burns frankincense, as he who blesses an idol. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Yes, they have chosen their own ways, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and their soul delights in their abominations: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "4", "sid": "ISA 66:4"}, "I also will choose their delusions, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will bring their fears on them; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["because when I called, no one answered; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["when I spoke, they didn\u2019t listen; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["but they did that which was evil in my eyes, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and chose that in which I didn\u2019t delight.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "5", "sid": "ISA 66:5"}, "Hear the LORD\u2019s word, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["you who tremble at his word: \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u201cYour brothers who hate you, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["who cast you out for my name\u2019s sake, have said, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["\u2018Let the LORD be glorified, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that we may see your joy;\u2019 \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["but it is those who shall be disappointed. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "6", "sid": "ISA 66:6"}, "A voice of tumult from the city, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a voice from the temple, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["a voice of the LORD that repays his enemies what they deserve.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "7", "sid": "ISA 66:7"}, "\u201cBefore she travailed, she gave birth. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Before her pain came, she delivered a son. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "8", "sid": "ISA 66:8"}, "Who has heard of such a thing? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Who has seen such things? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["Shall a land be born in one day? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Shall a nation be born at once? \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["For as soon as Zion travailed, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["she gave birth to her children. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "9", "sid": "ISA 66:9"}, "Shall I bring to the birth, and not cause to be delivered?\u201d says the LORD.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["\u201cShall I who cause to give birth shut the womb?\u201d says your Allah.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "10", "sid": "ISA 66:10"}, "\u201cRejoice with Jerusalem, and be glad for her, all you who love her.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["Rejoice for joy with her, all you who mourn over her; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "11", "sid": "ISA 66:11"}, "that you may nurse and be satisfied at the comforting breasts;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["that you may drink deeply, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and be delighted with the abundance of her glory.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "12", "sid": "ISA 66:12"}, "For the LORD says, \u201cBehold, I will extend peace to her like a river,\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and the glory of the nations like an overflowing stream; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and you will nurse. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["You will be carried on her side, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and will be dandled on her knees. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "13", "sid": "ISA 66:13"}, "As one whom his mother comforts, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["so I will comfort you. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["You will be comforted in Jerusalem.\u201d \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "14", "sid": "ISA 66:14"}, "You will see it, and your heart shall rejoice, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and your bones will flourish like the tender grass. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["The LORD\u2019s hand will be known amongst his servants; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and he will have indignation against his enemies. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "b"}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "15", "sid": "ISA 66:15"}, "For, behold, the LORD will come with fire, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his chariots will be like the whirlwind; \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": ["to render his anger with fierceness, \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and his rebuke with flames of fire. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q1", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "16", "sid": "ISA 66:16"}, "For the LORD will execute judgement by fire and by his sword on all flesh;\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "q2", "content": ["and those slain by the LORD will be many. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "17", "sid": "ISA 66:17"}, "\u201cThose who sanctify themselves and purify themselves to go to the gardens, behind one in the middle, eating pig\u2019s meat,\nabominable things, and the mouse, they shall come to an end together,\u201d says the LORD.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "18", "sid": "ISA 66:18"}, "\u201cFor I know their works and their thoughts. The time comes that I will gather all nations and languages, and they will\ncome, and will see my glory. \n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "19", "sid": "ISA 66:19"}, "\u201cI will set a sign amongst them, and I will send those who escape of them to the nations, to Tarshish, Pul, and Lud, who\ndraw the bow, to Tubal and Javan, to far-away islands, who have not heard my fame, nor have seen my glory; and they shall\ndeclare my glory amongst the nations. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "20", "sid": "ISA 66:20"}, "They shall bring all your brothers out of all the nations for an offering to the LORD, on horses, in chariots, in\nlitters, on mules, and on camels, to my holy mountain Jerusalem, says the LORD, as the children of Israel bring their offering\nin a clean vessel into the LORD\u2019s house. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "21", "sid": "ISA 66:21"}, "Of them I will also select priests and Levites,\u201d says the LORD.\n"]}, {"type": "para", "marker": "p", "content": [{"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "22", "sid": "ISA 66:22"}, "\u201cFor as the new heavens and the new earth, which I will make, shall remain before me,\u201d says the LORD, \u201cso your offspring\nand your name shall remain. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "23", "sid": "ISA 66:23"}, "It shall happen that from one new moon to another, and from one Sabbath to another, all flesh will come to worship before\nme,\u201d says the LORD. \n", {"type": "verse", "marker": "v", "number": "24", "sid": "ISA 66:24"}, "\u201cThey will go out, and look at the dead bodies of the men who have transgressed against me; for their worm will not die,\nnor will their fire be quenched, and they will be loathsome to all mankind.\u201d\n"]}]}